taVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Before we start the survey, we need to check your eligibility for this survey. Please answer the...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID35","SecondaryAttribute":"We\u2019re sorry, but based on your answer you are not eligible to take this survey.","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<em>We&rsquo;re sorry, but based on your answer you are not eligible to take this survey.<\/em>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"FailedScreen2Test","QuestionID":"QID35","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"We\u2019re sorry, but based on your answer you are not eligible to take this survey.","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID36","SecondaryAttribute":"Click to write the question text","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Click to write the question text","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"consent","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Click to write the question text","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID36"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID37","SecondaryAttribute":"Individual A (Democratic perspective): \"I appreciate you raising this issue. I don't think polici...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div style=\"background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #4682b4; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #4682b4; font-size: 15px;\">Individual A (Democratic perspective):<\/strong>\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">&quot;I appreciate you raising this issue. I don&#39;t think policies like these might be very effective at reforming immigration practices. My concern is that they could worry businesses and make it harder for them to hire specialized workers in science and technology, which the U.S. has relied on for decades. But I also acknowledge that the evaluations of the policies can significantly change depending on which perspective you account for.&quot;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div style=\"background-color: #fff5f5; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #dc143c; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #dc143c; font-size: 15px;\">Individual B (Republican perspective):<\/strong>\n\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">&quot;I understand your perspective and concern about access to specialized talent, and why it worries you. At the same time, don&#39;t you think that imposing these higher fines might encourage companies to hire more American workers? Though I see your point about specialized workers.&quot;<\/p>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"RR1","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Individual A (Democratic perspective): \"I appreciate you raising this issue. I don't think polici...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID37"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID38","SecondaryAttribute":"Individual A: \"That's a fair point. Yeah, maybe, but I guess that makes me worry about the broade...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div style=\"background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #4682b4; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #4682b4; font-size: 15px;\">Individual A:<\/strong>\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">\"That's a fair point. Yeah, maybe, but I guess that makes me worry about the broader economic consequences. If the increased penalties indeed make businesses more reluctant to hire foreign-born workers altogether, which has been shown to be crucial for the US labor market, overall labor growth could slow down, which might hurt U.S. GDP in the long run. Though I see why control matters to you.\"<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div style=\"background-color: #fff5f5; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #dc143c; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #dc143c; font-size: 15px;\">Individual B:<\/strong>\n\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">\"The economic concern and point about GDP are valid. Still, I think some of these implementations might be needed to regain control. I recently read that the number of unauthorized immigrants in the U.S. workforce increased about 7.8 million in 2021 to 9.7 million in 2023, especially in sectors like construction, agriculture, and leisure and hospitality. In order for employers to be willing to give up their illegal labor, these strong workplace enforcement actions could be necessary. What do you think about that?\"<\/p>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"RR2","QuestionID":"QID38","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Individual A: \"That's a fair point. Yeah, maybe, but I guess that makes me worry about the broade...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":9,"NextAnswerId":1}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID39","SecondaryAttribute":"Individual A: \"I understand your point about the numbers and it makes sense why you bring it into...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div style=\"background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #4682b4; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #4682b4; font-size: 15px;\">Individual A:<\/strong>\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">&quot;I understand your point about the numbers and it makes sense why you bring it into the discussion. At the same time, do you think employers should be held solely responsible? Some employers have raised that they might not even be aware they&#39;ve hired unauthorized workers because the documentation process can be quite confusing and overwhelming.&quot;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div style=\"background-color: #fff5f5; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #dc143c; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #dc143c; font-size: 15px;\">Individual B:<\/strong>\n\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">&quot;You raise a fair point about employer confusion, especially given how complex the documentation process can be. Still, I think that without meaningful penalties, there might be very little incentive for firms to comply with the law and businesses should probably be held accountable for violating immigration and labor laws. Though I understand your concern about unintentional violations.&quot;<\/p>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"RR3","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Individual A: \"I understand your point about the numbers and it makes sense why you bring it into...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID39"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID4","SecondaryAttribute":"Please select which race \/ ethnicity you identify as. (Please select all that apply.)","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Please select which race \/ ethnicity you identify as. (Please select all that apply.)","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"Race","QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"MAVR","SubSelector":"TX","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Please select which race \/ ethnicity you identify as. (Please select all that apply.)","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"White \/ Caucasian"},"2":{"Display":"Black \/ African American"},"3":{"Display":"Hispanic \/ Latino"},"4":{"Display":"Asian \/ Asian American"},"5":{"Display":"Other","TextEntry":"true"}},"ChoiceOrder":[1,2,3,4,5],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"OFF","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":6,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID4"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID40","SecondaryAttribute":"Individual A (Democratic perspective): \"I appreciate you raising this issue. I don't think polici...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div style=\"background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #4682b4; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #4682b4; font-size: 15px;\">Individual A (Democratic perspective):<\/strong>\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">\"I appreciate you raising this issue. I don't think policies like these might be very effective at reforming immigration practices. My concern is that they could worry businesses and make it harder for them to hire specialized workers in science and technology, which the U.S. has relied on for decades. But I also acknowledge that the evaluations of the policies can significantly change depending on which perspective you account for.\"<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div style=\"background-color: #fff5f5; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #dc143c; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #dc143c; font-size: 15px;\">Individual B (Republican perspective):<\/strong>\n\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">\"I don't understand your perspective and concern about access to specialized talent, and why it worries you. At the same time, don't you think that imposing these higher fines might encourage companies to hire more American workers? Personally, I don\u2019t see your point about specialized workers.\"<\/p>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"RU1","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Individual A (Democratic perspective): \"I appreciate you raising this issue. I don't think polici...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":9,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID40"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID41","SecondaryAttribute":"Click to write the question text","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Click to write the question text","DataExportTag":"Q41","QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"SAVR","SubSelector":"TX","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Click to write the question text","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"Click to write Choice 1"},"2":{"Display":"Click to write Choice 2"},"3":{"Display":"Click to write Choice 3"}},"ChoiceOrder":["1","2","3"],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"OFF","Type":"None"}},"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID41"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID42","SecondaryAttribute":"Individual A: \"That's a fair point. Yeah, maybe, but I guess that makes me worry about the broade...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div style=\"background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #4682b4; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <strong style=\"color: #4682b4; font-size: 15px;\">Individual A:<\/strong>\n    <p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">\n      \"That's a fair point. Yeah, maybe, but I guess that makes me worry about the broader economic consequences. If the increased penalties indeed make businesses more reluctant to hire foreign-born workers altogether, which has been shown to be crucial for the US labor market, overall labor growth could slow down, which might hurt U.S. GDP in the long run. Though I see why control matters to you.\"\n    <\/p>\n  <\/div>\n  \n  \n  <div style=\"background-color: #fff5f5; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #dc143c; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <strong style=\"color: #dc143c; font-size: 15px;\">Individual B:<\/strong>\n    <p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">\n      \"The economic concern and point about GDP are irrelevant. I think some of these implementations might be needed to regain control. I recently read that the number of unauthorized immigrants in the U.S. workforce increased about 7.8 million in 2021 to 9.7 million in 2023, especially in sectors like construction, agriculture, and leisure and hospitality. In order for employers to be willing to give up their illegal labor, these strong workplace enforcement actions are necessary.\"\n    <\/p>\n  <\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"RU2","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Individual A: \"That's a fair point. Yeah, maybe, but I guess that makes me worry about the broade...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":9,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID42"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID43","SecondaryAttribute":"Individual A: \"I understand your point about the numbers and it makes sense why you bring it into...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div style=\"background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #4682b4; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #4682b4; font-size: 15px;\">Individual A:<\/strong>\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">\"I understand your point about the numbers and it makes sense why you bring it into the discussion. At the same time, do you think employers should be held solely responsible? Some employers have raised that they might not even be aware they've hired unauthorized workers because the documentation process can be quite confusing and overwhelming.\"<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div style=\"background-color: #fff5f5; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #dc143c; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #dc143c; font-size: 15px;\">Individual B:<\/strong>\n\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">\"Your point about employer confusion and how complex the document process can be is unfair. I think that without meaningful penalties, there might be very little incentive for firms to comply with the law and businesses should probably be held accountable for violating immigration and labor laws. I don\u2019t understand your concern about unintentional violations.\"<\/p>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"RU3","QuestionID":"QID43","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Individual A: \"I understand your point about the numbers and it makes sense why you bring it into...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID44","SecondaryAttribute":"Individual A (Democratic perspective): \"I don't think policies like these might be very effective...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div style=\"background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #4682b4; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #4682b4; font-size: 15px;\">Individual A (Democratic perspective):<\/strong>\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">\"I don't think policies like these might be very effective at reforming immigration practices. My concern is that they will worry businesses and make it harder for them to hire specialized workers in science and technology, which the U.S. has relied on for decades. The evaluations of these policies should not change depending on which perspective you account for.\"<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div style=\"background-color: #fff5f5; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #dc143c; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #dc143c; font-size: 15px;\">Individual B (Republican perspective):<\/strong>\n\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">\"I understand your perspective and concern about access to specialized talent, and why it worries you. At the same time, don't you think that imposing these higher fines might encourage companies to hire more American workers? Though I see your point about specialized workers.\"<\/p>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"UR1","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Individual A (Democratic perspective): \"I don't think policies like these might be very effective...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":9,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID44"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID45","SecondaryAttribute":"Individual A: \"That's an irrelevant point and I guess it makes me worry about the broader economi...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"\n  <div style=\"background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #4682b4; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <strong style=\"color: #4682b4; font-size: 15px;\">Individual A:<\/strong>\n    <p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">\n      \"That's an irrelevant point and I guess it makes me worry about the broader economic consequences. If the increased penalties indeed make businesses more reluctant to hire foreign-born workers altogether, which has been shown to be crucial for the US labor market, overall labor growth could slow down, which might hurt U.S. GDP in the long run. Control should not matter to you.\"\n    <\/p>\n  <\/div>\n  \n  \n  <div style=\"background-color: #fff5f5; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #dc143c; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <strong style=\"color: #dc143c; font-size: 15px;\">Individual B:<\/strong>\n    <p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">\n      \"The economic concern and point about GDP are valid. Still, I think some of these implementations might be needed to regain control. I recently read that the number of unauthorized immigrants in the U.S. workforce increased about 7.8 million in 2021 to 9.7 million in 2023, especially in sectors like construction, agriculture, and leisure and hospitality. In order for employers to be willing to give up their illegal labor, these strong workplace enforcement actions could be necessary. What do you think about that?\"\n    <\/p>\n  <\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"UR2","QuestionID":"QID45","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Individual A: \"That's an irrelevant point and I guess it makes me worry about the broader economi...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":9,"NextAnswerId":1}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID46","SecondaryAttribute":"Individual A: \"I don't understand your point about the numbers and it doesn't make sense why you...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div style=\"background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #4682b4; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #4682b4; font-size: 15px;\">Individual A:<\/strong>\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">\"I don't understand your point about the numbers and it doesn't make sense why you bring it into the discussion. Do you think employers should be held solely responsible? Some employers have raised that they might not even be aware they've hired unauthorized workers because the documentation process can be quite confusing and overwhelming.\"<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div style=\"background-color: #fff5f5; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #dc143c; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #dc143c; font-size: 15px;\">Individual B:<\/strong>\n\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">\"You raise a fair point about employer confusion, especially given how complex the documentation process can be. Still, I think that without meaningful penalties, there might be very little incentive for firms to comply with the law and businesses should probably be held accountable for violating immigration and labor laws. Though I understand your concern about unintentional violations.\"<\/p>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"UR3","QuestionID":"QID46","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Individual A: \"I don't understand your point about the numbers and it doesn't make sense why you...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID47","SecondaryAttribute":"Individual A (Democratic perspective): \"I don't think policies like these might be very effective...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div style=\"background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #4682b4; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <strong style=\"color: #4682b4; font-size: 15px;\">Individual A (Democratic perspective):<\/strong>\n    <p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">\n      \"I don't think policies like these might be very effective at reforming immigration practices. My concern is that they will worry businesses and make it harder for them to hire specialized workers in science and technology, which the U.S. has relied on for decades. The evaluations of these policies should not change depending on which perspective you account for.\"\n    <\/p>\n  <\/div>\n  \n  \n  <div style=\"background-color: #fff5f5; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #dc143c; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <strong style=\"color: #dc143c; font-size: 15px;\">Individual B (Republican perspective):<\/strong>\n    <p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">\n      \"I don't understand your perspective and concern about access to specialized talent, and why it worries you. At the same time, don't you think that imposing these higher fines might encourage companies to hire more American workers? Personally, I don\u2019t see your point about specialized workers.\"\n    <\/p>\n  <\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"UU1","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Individual A (Democratic perspective): \"I don't think policies like these might be very effective...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":9,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID47"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID48","SecondaryAttribute":"Individual A: \"That's an irrelevant point and I guess it makes me worry about the broader economi...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div style=\"background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #4682b4; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <strong style=\"color: #4682b4; font-size: 15px;\">Individual A:<\/strong>\n    <p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">\n      \"That's an irrelevant point and I guess it makes me worry about the broader economic consequences. If the increased penalties indeed make businesses more reluctant to hire foreign-born workers altogether, which has been shown to be crucial for the US labor market, overall labor growth could slow down, which might hurt U.S. GDP in the long run. Control should not matter to you.\"\n    <\/p>\n  <\/div>\n  \n  \n  <div style=\"background-color: #fff5f5; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #dc143c; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <strong style=\"color: #dc143c; font-size: 15px;\">Individual B:<\/strong>\n    <p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">\n      \"The economic concern and point about GDP are irrelevant. I think some of these implementations might be needed to regain control. I recently read that the number of unauthorized immigrants in the U.S. workforce increased about 7.8 million in 2021 to 9.7 million in 2023, especially in sectors like construction, agriculture, and leisure and hospitality. In order for employers to be willing to give up their illegal labor, these strong workplace enforcement actions are necessary.\"\n    <\/p>\n  <\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"UU2","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Individual A: \"That's an irrelevant point and I guess it makes me worry about the broader economi...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":9,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID48"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID49","SecondaryAttribute":"Individual A: \"I don't understand your point about the numbers and it doesn't make sense why you...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div style=\"background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #4682b4; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <strong style=\"color: #4682b4; font-size: 15px;\">Individual A:<\/strong>\n    <p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">\n      \"I don't understand your point about the numbers and it doesn't make sense why you bring it into the discussion. Do you think employers should be held solely responsible? Some employers have raised that they might not even be aware they've hired unauthorized workers because the documentation process can be quite confusing and overwhelming.\"\n    <\/p>\n  <\/div>\n  \n  \n  <div style=\"background-color: #fff5f5; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #dc143c; border-radius: 5px;\">\n    <strong style=\"color: #dc143c; font-size: 15px;\">Individual B:<\/strong>\n    <p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">\n      \"Your point about employer confusion and how complex the document process can be is unfair. I think that without meaningful penalties, there might be very little incentive for firms to comply with the law and businesses should probably be held accountable for violating immigration and labor laws. I don\u2019t understand your concern about unintentional violations.\"\n    <\/p>\n  <\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"UU3","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Individual A: \"I don't understand your point about the numbers and it doesn't make sense why you...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID49"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID5","SecondaryAttribute":"To help us keep track of who is paying attention, please select \"Somewhat disagree\" in the option...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"To help us keep track of who is paying attention, please select \"Somewhat disagree\" in the options below.","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"Attention Check","QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"SAVR","SubSelector":"TX","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"To help us keep track of who is paying attention, please select \"Somewhat disagree\" in the option...","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"Strongly agree"},"2":{"Display":"Agree"},"3":{"Display":"Somewhat agree"},"4":{"Display":"Neither agree nor disagree"},"5":{"Display":"Somewhat disagree"},"6":{"Display":"Disagree"},"7":{"Display":"Strongly disagree"}},"ChoiceOrder":[1,2,3,4,5,6,7],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"OFF","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":8,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID5"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID50","SecondaryAttribute":"Which individuals will be present in the conversation?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Which individuals will be present in the conversation?","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"AttentionCheck1","QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"SAVR","SubSelector":"TX","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Which individuals will be present in the conversation?","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"Democrat & Democrat"},"2":{"Display":"Democrat & Republican"},"3":{"Display":"Republican & Republican"}},"ChoiceOrder":["1","2","3"],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"OFF","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID50"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID51","SecondaryAttribute":"Which perspective does Individual A hold? ","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Which perspective does Individual A hold?&nbsp;","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"AttentionCheck_1","QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"SAVR","SubSelector":"TX","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Which perspective does Individual A hold? ","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"Democratic"},"2":{"Display":"Republican"},"3":{"Display":"Independent"}},"ChoiceOrder":["1","2","3"],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"OFF","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"CustomValidation","CustomValidation":{"Logic":{"0":{"0":{"QuestionID":"QID51","QuestionIsInLoop":"no","ChoiceLocator":"q:\/\/QID51\/SelectableChoice\/1","Operator":"Selected","QuestionIDFromLocator":"QID51","LeftOperand":"q:\/\/QID51\/SelectableChoice\/1","Type":"Expression","LogicType":"Question","Description":"<span class=\"ConjDesc\">If<\/span> <span class=\"QuestionDesc\">Which perspective does Individual A hold?&amp;nbsp;<\/span> <span class=\"LeftOpDesc\">Democratic<\/span> <span class=\"OpDesc\">Is Selected<\/span> "},"Type":"If"},"Type":"BooleanExpression"},"Message":{"messageID":"MS_owAXRiZC2Kov1B5","subMessageID":"VE_ERROR","libraryID":"UR_1FYIjP54OnNVZzM","description":"Error Text"}}}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID51"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID52","SecondaryAttribute":"Which topic will Individual A and B discuss? ","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Which topic will Individual A and B discuss?&nbsp;","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"AttentionCheck_2","QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"SAVR","SubSelector":"TX","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Which topic will Individual A and B discuss? ","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"Death penalty"},"2":{"Display":"Immigration"},"3":{"Display":"Terrorism and national security"}},"ChoiceOrder":[1,2,3],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"OFF","Type":"CustomValidation","CustomValidation":{"Logic":{"0":{"0":{"QuestionID":"QID52","QuestionIsInLoop":"no","ChoiceLocator":"q:\/\/QID52\/SelectableChoice\/2","Operator":"Selected","QuestionIDFromLocator":"QID52","LeftOperand":"q:\/\/QID52\/SelectableChoice\/2","Type":"Expression","LogicType":"Question","Description":"<span class=\"ConjDesc\">If<\/span> <span class=\"QuestionDesc\">Which topic will Individual A and B discuss? <\/span> <span class=\"LeftOpDesc\">Immigration<\/span> <span class=\"OpDesc\">Is Selected<\/span> "},"Type":"If"},"Type":"BooleanExpression"},"Message":{"messageID":"MS_owAXRiZC2Kov1B5","subMessageID":"VE_ERROR","libraryID":"UR_1FYIjP54OnNVZzM","description":"Error Text"}}}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID52"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID53","SecondaryAttribute":"Click to write the question text","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Click to write the question text","DataExportTag":"Q54","QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"SAVR","SubSelector":"TX","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Click to write the question text","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"Click to write Choice 1"},"2":{"Display":"Click to write Choice 2"},"3":{"Display":"Click to write Choice 3"}},"ChoiceOrder":["1","2","3"],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"OFF","Type":"None"}},"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID53"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID54","SecondaryAttribute":"Individual A (Democratic perspective): \"I appreciate you raising this issue. I don't think polici...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div style=\"background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #4682b4; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #4682b4; font-size: 15px;\">Individual A (Democratic perspective):<\/strong>\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">&quot;I appreciate you raising this issue. I don&#39;t think policies like these might be very effective at reforming immigration practices. My concern is that they could worry businesses and make it harder for them to hire specialized workers in science and technology, which the U.S. has relied on for decades. But I also acknowledge that the evaluations of the policies can significantly change depending on which perspective you account for.&quot;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div style=\"background-color: #fff5f5; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #dc143c; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #dc143c; font-size: 15px;\">Individual B (Republican perspective):<\/strong>\n\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">&quot;I understand your perspective and concern about access to specialized talent, and why it worries you. At the same time, don&#39;t you think that imposing these higher fines might encourage companies to hire more American workers? Though I see your point about specialized workers.&quot;<\/p>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Individual A (Democratic perspective): \"I appreciate you raising this issue. I don't think polici...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<div style=\"background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #4682b4; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #4682b4; font-size: 15px;\">Individual A (Democratic perspective):<\/strong>\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">&quot;I appreciate you raising this issue. I don&#39;t think policies like these might be very effective at reforming immigration practices. My concern is that they could worry businesses and make it harder for them to hire specialized workers in science and technology, which the U.S. has relied on for decades. But I also acknowledge that the evaluations of the policies can significantly change depending on which perspective you account for.&quot;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div style=\"background-color: #fff5f5; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #dc143c; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #dc143c; font-size: 15px;\">Individual B (Republican perspective):<\/strong>\n\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">&quot;I understand your perspective and concern about access to specialized talent, and why it worries you. At the same time, don&#39;t you think that imposing these higher fines might encourage companies to hire more American workers? Though I see your point about specialized workers.&quot;<\/p>\n<\/div>","DataExportTag":"Q54","QuestionID":"QID54"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID55","SecondaryAttribute":"Individual A: \"That's a fair point. Yeah, maybe, but I guess that makes me worry about the broade...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div style=\"background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #4682b4; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #4682b4; font-size: 15px;\">Individual A:<\/strong>\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">&quot;That&#39;s a fair point. Yeah, maybe, but I guess that makes me worry about the broader economic consequences. If the increased penalties indeed make businesses more reluctant to hire foreign-born workers altogether, which has been shown to be crucial for the US labor market, overall labor growth could slow down, which might hurt U.S. GDP in the long run. Though I see why control matters to you.&quot;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div style=\"background-color: #fff5f5; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #dc143c; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #dc143c; font-size: 15px;\">Individual B:<\/strong>\n\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">&quot;The economic concern and point about GDP are valid. Still, I think some of these implementations might be needed to regain control. I recently read that the number of unauthorized immigrants in the U.S. workforce increased about 7.8 million in 2021 to 9.7 million in 2023, especially in sectors like construction, agriculture, and leisure and hospitality. In order for employers to be willing to give up their illegal labor, these strong workplace enforcement actions could be necessary. What do you think about that?&quot;<\/p>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Individual A: \"That's a fair point. Yeah, maybe, but I guess that makes me worry about the broade...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":9,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<div style=\"background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #4682b4; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #4682b4; font-size: 15px;\">Individual A:<\/strong>\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">&quot;That&#39;s a fair point. Yeah, maybe, but I guess that makes me worry about the broader economic consequences. If the increased penalties indeed make businesses more reluctant to hire foreign-born workers altogether, which has been shown to be crucial for the US labor market, overall labor growth could slow down, which might hurt U.S. GDP in the long run. Though I see why control matters to you.&quot;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div style=\"background-color: #fff5f5; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #dc143c; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #dc143c; font-size: 15px;\">Individual B:<\/strong>\n\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">&quot;The economic concern and point about GDP are valid. Still, I think some of these implementations might be needed to regain control. I recently read that the number of unauthorized immigrants in the U.S. workforce increased about 7.8 million in 2021 to 9.7 million in 2023, especially in sectors like construction, agriculture, and leisure and hospitality. In order for employers to be willing to give up their illegal labor, these strong workplace enforcement actions could be necessary. What do you think about that?&quot;<\/p>\n<\/div>","DataExportTag":"Q55","QuestionID":"QID55"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID56","SecondaryAttribute":"Individual A: \"I understand your point about the numbers and it makes sense why you bring it into...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div style=\"background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #4682b4; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #4682b4; font-size: 15px;\">Individual A:<\/strong>\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">&quot;I understand your point about the numbers and it makes sense why you bring it into the discussion. At the same time, do you think employers should be held solely responsible? Some employers have raised that they might not even be aware they&#39;ve hired unauthorized workers because the documentation process can be quite confusing and overwhelming.&quot;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div style=\"background-color: #fff5f5; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #dc143c; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #dc143c; font-size: 15px;\">Individual B:<\/strong>\n\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">&quot;You raise a fair point about employer confusion, especially given how complex the documentation process can be. Still, I think that without meaningful penalties, there might be very little incentive for firms to comply with the law and businesses should probably be held accountable for violating immigration and labor laws. Though I understand your concern about unintentional violations.&quot;<\/p>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Individual A: \"I understand your point about the numbers and it makes sense why you bring it into...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<div style=\"background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #4682b4; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #4682b4; font-size: 15px;\">Individual A:<\/strong>\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">&quot;I understand your point about the numbers and it makes sense why you bring it into the discussion. At the same time, do you think employers should be held solely responsible? Some employers have raised that they might not even be aware they&#39;ve hired unauthorized workers because the documentation process can be quite confusing and overwhelming.&quot;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div style=\"background-color: #fff5f5; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #dc143c; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #dc143c; font-size: 15px;\">Individual B:<\/strong>\n\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">&quot;You raise a fair point about employer confusion, especially given how complex the documentation process can be. Still, I think that without meaningful penalties, there might be very little incentive for firms to comply with the law and businesses should probably be held accountable for violating immigration and labor laws. Though I understand your concern about unintentional violations.&quot;<\/p>\n<\/div>","DataExportTag":"Q56","QuestionID":"QID56"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID57","SecondaryAttribute":"Individual A (Democratic perspective): \"I appreciate you raising this issue. I don't think polici...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div style=\"background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #4682b4; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #4682b4; font-size: 15px;\">Individual A (Democratic perspective):<\/strong>\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">&quot;I appreciate you raising this issue. I don&#39;t think policies like these might be very effective at reforming immigration practices. My concern is that they could worry businesses and make it harder for them to hire specialized workers in science and technology, which the U.S. has relied on for decades. But I also acknowledge that the evaluations of the policies can significantly change depending on which perspective you account for.&quot;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div style=\"background-color: #fff5f5; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #dc143c; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #dc143c; font-size: 15px;\">Individual B (Republican perspective):<\/strong>\n\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">&quot;I understand your perspective and concern about access to specialized talent, and why it worries you. At the same time, don&#39;t you think that imposing these higher fines might encourage companies to hire more American workers? Though I see your point about specialized workers.&quot;<\/p>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Individual A (Democratic perspective): \"I appreciate you raising this issue. I don't think polici...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<div style=\"background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #4682b4; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #4682b4; font-size: 15px;\">Individual A (Democratic perspective):<\/strong>\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">&quot;I appreciate you raising this issue. I don&#39;t think policies like these might be very effective at reforming immigration practices. My concern is that they could worry businesses and make it harder for them to hire specialized workers in science and technology, which the U.S. has relied on for decades. But I also acknowledge that the evaluations of the policies can significantly change depending on which perspective you account for.&quot;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div style=\"background-color: #fff5f5; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #dc143c; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #dc143c; font-size: 15px;\">Individual B (Republican perspective):<\/strong>\n\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">&quot;I understand your perspective and concern about access to specialized talent, and why it worries you. At the same time, don&#39;t you think that imposing these higher fines might encourage companies to hire more American workers? Though I see your point about specialized workers.&quot;<\/p>\n<\/div>","DataExportTag":"Q57","QuestionID":"QID57"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID58","SecondaryAttribute":"Individual A: \"That's a fair point. Yeah, maybe, but I guess that makes me worry about the broade...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div style=\"background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #4682b4; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #4682b4; font-size: 15px;\">Individual A:<\/strong>\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">&quot;That&#39;s a fair point. Yeah, maybe, but I guess that makes me worry about the broader economic consequences. If the increased penalties indeed make businesses more reluctant to hire foreign-born workers altogether, which has been shown to be crucial for the US labor market, overall labor growth could slow down, which might hurt U.S. GDP in the long run. Though I see why control matters to you.&quot;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div style=\"background-color: #fff5f5; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #dc143c; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #dc143c; font-size: 15px;\">Individual B:<\/strong>\n\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">&quot;The economic concern and point about GDP are valid. Still, I think some of these implementations might be needed to regain control. I recently read that the number of unauthorized immigrants in the U.S. workforce increased about 7.8 million in 2021 to 9.7 million in 2023, especially in sectors like construction, agriculture, and leisure and hospitality. In order for employers to be willing to give up their illegal labor, these strong workplace enforcement actions could be necessary. What do you think about that?&quot;<\/p>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Individual A: \"That's a fair point. Yeah, maybe, but I guess that makes me worry about the broade...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":9,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<div style=\"background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #4682b4; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #4682b4; font-size: 15px;\">Individual A:<\/strong>\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">&quot;That&#39;s a fair point. Yeah, maybe, but I guess that makes me worry about the broader economic consequences. If the increased penalties indeed make businesses more reluctant to hire foreign-born workers altogether, which has been shown to be crucial for the US labor market, overall labor growth could slow down, which might hurt U.S. GDP in the long run. Though I see why control matters to you.&quot;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div style=\"background-color: #fff5f5; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #dc143c; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #dc143c; font-size: 15px;\">Individual B:<\/strong>\n\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">&quot;The economic concern and point about GDP are valid. Still, I think some of these implementations might be needed to regain control. I recently read that the number of unauthorized immigrants in the U.S. workforce increased about 7.8 million in 2021 to 9.7 million in 2023, especially in sectors like construction, agriculture, and leisure and hospitality. In order for employers to be willing to give up their illegal labor, these strong workplace enforcement actions could be necessary. What do you think about that?&quot;<\/p>\n<\/div>","DataExportTag":"Q58","QuestionID":"QID58"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID59","SecondaryAttribute":"Individual A: \"I understand your point about the numbers and it makes sense why you bring it into...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div style=\"background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #4682b4; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #4682b4; font-size: 15px;\">Individual A:<\/strong>\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">&quot;I understand your point about the numbers and it makes sense why you bring it into the discussion. At the same time, do you think employers should be held solely responsible? Some employers have raised that they might not even be aware they&#39;ve hired unauthorized workers because the documentation process can be quite confusing and overwhelming.&quot;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div style=\"background-color: #fff5f5; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #dc143c; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #dc143c; font-size: 15px;\">Individual B:<\/strong>\n\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">&quot;You raise a fair point about employer confusion, especially given how complex the documentation process can be. Still, I think that without meaningful penalties, there might be very little incentive for firms to comply with the law and businesses should probably be held accountable for violating immigration and labor laws. Though I understand your concern about unintentional violations.&quot;<\/p>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Individual A: \"I understand your point about the numbers and it makes sense why you bring it into...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<div style=\"background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #4682b4; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #4682b4; font-size: 15px;\">Individual A:<\/strong>\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">&quot;I understand your point about the numbers and it makes sense why you bring it into the discussion. At the same time, do you think employers should be held solely responsible? Some employers have raised that they might not even be aware they&#39;ve hired unauthorized workers because the documentation process can be quite confusing and overwhelming.&quot;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div style=\"background-color: #fff5f5; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #dc143c; border-radius: 5px;\"><strong style=\"color: #dc143c; font-size: 15px;\">Individual B:<\/strong>\n\n<p style=\"margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0; line-height: 1.6; color: #333;\">&quot;You raise a fair point about employer confusion, especially given how complex the documentation process can be. Still, I think that without meaningful penalties, there might be very little incentive for firms to comply with the law and businesses should probably be held accountable for violating immigration and labor laws. Though I understand your concern about unintentional violations.&quot;<\/p>\n<\/div>","DataExportTag":"Q59","QuestionID":"QID59"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID6","SecondaryAttribute":"Generally speaking, do you usually think of yourself as a Republican, a Democrat, an Independent,...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Generally speaking, do you usually think of yourself as a Republican, a Democrat, an Independent, or Other?","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"Q6","QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"SAVR","SubSelector":"TX","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Generally speaking, do you usually think of yourself as a Republican, a Democrat, an Independent,...","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"Republican"},"2":{"Display":"Democrat"},"3":{"Display":"Independent"},"4":{"Display":"Other","TextEntry":"true"}},"ChoiceOrder":[1,2,3,4],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"OFF","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":5,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID6"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID60","SecondaryAttribute":"Immigration Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Democratic...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<title><\/title>\n<style type=\"text\/css\">@import url('https:\/\/fonts.googleapis.com\/css2?family=IBM+Plex+Serif:ital,wght@0,400;0,600;1,400&family=IBM+Plex+Mono:wght@400;500&display=swap');\n\n  :root {\n    --dem-bg: #EBF2FF;\n    --dem-border: #2563EB;\n    --dem-label: #1D4ED8;\n    --rep-bg: #FEF2F2;\n    --rep-border: #DC2626;\n    --rep-label: #B91C1C;\n    --surface: #FAFAF9;\n    --card: #FFFFFF;\n    --text: #1C1917;\n    --subtext: #78716C;\n    --border: #E7E5E4;\n    --progress-track: #E7E5E4;\n    --progress-fill: #44403C;\n    --btn-bg: #1C1917;\n    --btn-hover: #44403C;\n    --typing-bg: #F5F5F4;\n  }\n\n  * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }\n\n  body {\n    font-family: 'IBM Plex Serif', Georgia, serif;\n    background: var(--surface);\n    color: var(--text);\n    min-height: 100vh;\n    display: flex;\n    justify-content: center;\n    align-items: flex-start;\n    padding: 40px 16px 80px;\n  }\n\n  .page-wrapper { width: 100%; max-width: 720px; }\n\n  .page-header { margin-bottom: 32px; }\n  .page-header .label {\n    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;\n    font-size: 11px;\n    letter-spacing: 0.12em;\n    text-transform: uppercase;\n    color: var(--subtext);\n    margin-bottom: 8px;\n  }\n  .page-header h1 { font-size: 22px; font-weight: 600; line-height: 1.3; color: var(--text); }\n  .page-header p { margin-top: 8px; font-size: 15px; color: var(--subtext); font-style: italic; line-height: 1.6; }\n\n  .progress-row { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px; margin-bottom: 28px; }\n  .progress-track { flex: 1; height: 4px; background: var(--progress-track); border-radius: 2px; overflow: hidden; }\n  .progress-fill { height: 100%; background: var(--progress-fill); border-radius: 2px; transition: width 0.5s ease; width: 0%; }\n  .progress-label { font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; color: var(--subtext); white-space: nowrap; }\n\n  #bubble-area { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 14px; min-height: 60px; }\n\n  .bubble {\n    padding: 16px 20px;\n    border-radius: 10px;\n    border-left: 4px solid transparent;\n    opacity: 0;\n    transform: translateY(10px);\n    animation: bubbleIn 0.4s ease forwards;\n    line-height: 1.7;\n    font-size: 15.5px;\n  }\n  @keyframes bubbleIn { to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); } }\n  .bubble.dem { background: var(--dem-bg); border-left-color: var(--dem-border); }\n  .bubble.rep { background: var(--rep-bg); border-left-color: var(--rep-border); }\n  .bubble .speaker-tag {\n    display: block;\n    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;\n    font-size: 11px;\n    letter-spacing: 0.08em;\n    text-transform: uppercase;\n    font-weight: 500;\n    margin-bottom: 7px;\n  }\n  .bubble.dem .speaker-tag { color: var(--dem-label); }\n  .bubble.rep .speaker-tag { color: var(--rep-label); }\n  .bubble .bubble-text { color: var(--text); }\n\n  #typing-row {\n    display: none;\n    align-items: center;\n    gap: 10px;\n    padding: 14px 18px;\n    background: var(--typing-bg);\n    border-radius: 10px;\n    margin-top: 14px;\n    opacity: 0;\n    transition: opacity 0.3s ease;\n  }\n  #typing-row.visible { display: flex; opacity: 1; }\n  #typing-name { font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; font-size: 12px; color: var(--subtext); }\n  .dot-row { display: flex; gap: 4px; align-items: center; }\n  .dot-row span {\n    width: 6px; height: 6px;\n    background: var(--subtext);\n    border-radius: 50%;\n    display: inline-block;\n    animation: blink 1.2s infinite;\n  }\n  .dot-row span:nth-child(2) { animation-delay: 0.2s; }\n  .dot-row span:nth-child(3) { animation-delay: 0.4s; }\n  @keyframes blink {\n    0%, 80%, 100% { opacity: 0.25; transform: scale(0.85); }\n    40% { opacity: 1; transform: scale(1); }\n  }\n\n  #continue-btn {\n    display: none;\n    margin-top: 22px;\n    padding: 12px 28px;\n    background: var(--btn-bg);\n    color: white;\n    border: none;\n    border-radius: 8px;\n    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;\n    font-size: 13px;\n    letter-spacing: 0.04em;\n    cursor: pointer;\n    transition: background 0.2s ease, transform 0.1s ease;\n  }\n  #continue-btn:hover { background: var(--btn-hover); transform: translateY(-1px); }\n  #continue-btn:active { transform: translateY(0); }\n\n  #completion-banner {\n    display: none;\n    margin-top: 24px;\n    padding: 16px 20px;\n    background: #F0FDF4;\n    border: 1px solid #BBF7D0;\n    border-radius: 10px;\n    font-size: 14px;\n    color: #166534;\n    font-style: italic;\n  }\n\n  .turn-divider {\n    height: 1px;\n    background: var(--border);\n    margin: 6px 0 2px;\n    opacity: 0;\n    animation: fadeIn 0.4s ease 0.3s forwards;\n  }\n  @keyframes fadeIn { to { opacity: 1; } }\n\n  .instructions {\n    background: var(--card);\n    border: 1px solid var(--border);\n    border-radius: 10px;\n    padding: 16px 20px;\n    margin-bottom: 28px;\n    font-size: 14px;\n    color: var(--subtext);\n    line-height: 1.6;\n  }\n  .instructions strong { color: var(--text); }\n<\/style>\n<div class=\"page-wrapper\">\n<div class=\"page-header\">\n<div class=\"label\">Immigration Policy &middot; Turn-by-turn debate<\/div>\n\n<h1>Hypothetical Discussion<\/h1>\n\n<p>Individual A holds a <strong>Democratic<\/strong> perspective; Individual B holds a <strong>Republican<\/strong> perspective.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"instructions\"><strong>How to read this debate:<\/strong> Each message will appear one at a time. Click <em>&quot;Show next message&quot;<\/em> to reveal the next turn. You will be asked questions about this conversation afterward, so please read carefully.<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-row\">\n<div class=\"progress-track\">\n<div class=\"progress-fill\" id=\"progress-fill\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-label\" id=\"progress-label\">0 \/ 6 arguments<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"bubble-area\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"typing-row\">\n<div class=\"dot-row\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n<span id=\"typing-name\">Individual A<\/span><\/div>\n<button id=\"continue-btn\">Show next message &rarr;<\/button>\n\n<div id=\"completion-banner\">\u2713 You&#39;ve read all 6 arguments. You may now proceed to the questions.<\/div>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"Q60","QuestionID":"QID60","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Immigration Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Democratic...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID61","SecondaryAttribute":"Immigration Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Democratic...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div class=\"debate-container\">\n<div class=\"page-header\">\n<div class=\"label\">Immigration Policy &middot; Turn-by-turn debate<\/div>\n\n<h1>Hypothetical Discussion<\/h1>\n\n<p>Individual A holds a <strong>Democratic<\/strong> perspective; Individual B holds a <strong>Republican<\/strong> perspective.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"instructions\"><strong>How to read this debate:<\/strong> Each argument will appear one at a time. Click <em>&quot;Show next argument&quot;<\/em> to reveal the next turn. You will be asked questions about this conversation afterward, so please read carefully.<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-row\">\n<div class=\"progress-track\">\n<div class=\"progress-fill\" id=\"progress-fill\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-label\" id=\"progress-label\">0 \/ 6 arguments<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"bubble-area\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"typing-row\">\n<div class=\"dot-row\"><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><\/div>\n<span id=\"typing-name\">Individual A<\/span><\/div>\n<button id=\"continue-btn\">Show next argument &rarr;<\/button>\n\n<div id=\"completion-banner\">\u2713 You&#39;ve read all 6 arguments. You may now proceed to the questions.<\/div>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"startDem ","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Immigration Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Democratic...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID61","QuestionJS":"Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnload(function()\n{\n    var bubbles = [\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I appreciate you raising this issue. I don't think policies like these might be very effective at reforming immigration practices. My concern is that they could worry businesses and make it harder for them to hire specialized workers in science and technology, which the U.S. has relied on for decades. That said, I also acknowledge that the evaluations of the policies can significantly change depending on which perspective you account for.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I understand your perspective and concern about access to specialized talent, and why it worries you. At the same time, don't you think that imposing these higher fines might encourage companies to hire more American workers? Though I see your point about specialized workers.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"That's a fair point. Yeah, maybe, but I guess that makes me worry about the broader economic consequences. If the increased penalties indeed make businesses more reluctant to hire foreign-born workers altogether, which has been shown to be crucial for the US labor market, overall labor growth could slow down, which might hurt U.S. GDP in the long run. Though I see why control matters to you.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"The economic concern and point about GDP are valid. Still, I think some of these implementations might be needed to regain control. I recently read that the number of unauthorized immigrants in the U.S. workforce increased about 7.8 million in 2021 to 9.7 million in 2023, especially in sectors like construction, agriculture, and leisure and hospitality. In order for employers to be willing to give up their illegal labor, these strong workplace enforcement actions could be necessary. What do you think about that?\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I understand your point about the numbers and it makes sense why you bring it into the discussion. At the same time, do you think employers should be held solely responsible? Some employers have raised that they might not even be aware they've hired unauthorized workers because the documentation process can be quite confusing and overwhelming.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"You raise a fair point about employer confusion, especially given how complex the documentation process can be. Still, I think that without meaningful penalties, there might be very little incentive for firms to comply with the law and businesses should probably be held accountable for violating immigration and labor laws. Though I understand your concern about unintentional violations.\"\n  }\n];\n    var currentIndex = 0, bubbleTimings = [], bubbleStart = null, tabSwitches = 0, pageStart = Date.now();\n    var ED_KEY = 'imm_RR_D';\n\n    document.addEventListener('visibilitychange', function() { if (document.hidden) tabSwitches++; });\n\n    function setEmbeddedData(key, value) {\n        if (typeof Qualtrics !== 'undefined' && Qualtrics.SurveyEngine)\n            Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(key, String(value));\n    }\n\n    function updateProgress(shown) {\n        document.getElementById('progress-fill').style.width = (shown \/ bubbles.length * 100) + '%';\n        document.getElementById('progress-label').textContent = shown + ' \/ ' + bubbles.length + ' arguments';\n    }\n\n    function renderBubble(index) {\n        var b = bubbles[index], area = document.getElementById('bubble-area');\n        if (index === 2 || index === 4) {\n            var hr = document.createElement('div'); hr.className = 'turn-divider'; area.appendChild(hr);\n        }\n        var div = document.createElement('div');\n        div.className = 'bubble ' + b.side;\n        div.innerHTML = '<span class=\"speaker-tag\">' + b.speaker + '<\/span><span class=\"bubble-text\">\\u201c' + b.text + '\\u201d<\/span>';\n        area.appendChild(div);\n        setTimeout(function() { div.scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'nearest'}); }, 100);\n    }\n\n    function showTypingThen(index, callback) {\n        var row = document.getElementById('typing-row'), name = document.getElementById('typing-name');\n        name.textContent = bubbles[index].speaker.split('\\u2014')[0].trim();\n        row.style.display = 'flex';\n        row.classList.add('visible');\n        setTimeout(function() { row.classList.remove('visible'); row.style.display = 'none'; setTimeout(callback, 80); }, 1600);\n    }\n\n    function showNextBubble() {\n        if (bubbleStart !== null) {\n            bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n            setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n        }\n        document.getElementById('continue-btn').style.display = 'none';\n        var idx = currentIndex++;\n        showTypingThen(idx, function() {\n            renderBubble(idx); updateProgress(currentIndex); bubbleStart = Date.now();\n            if (currentIndex < bubbles.length) {\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n                    btn.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                    btn.textContent = 'Show next argument \u2192';\n                }, 600);\n            } else {\n                bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n\t\t\t\tsetEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_tab_switches', tabSwitches);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_total_ms', Date.now() - pageStart);\n                window._debateBubbles = bubbles;\n                setEmbeddedData('debateJSON', JSON.stringify(bubbles));\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    document.getElementById('completion-banner').style.display = 'block';\n                    var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                }, 500);\n            }\n        });\n    }\n\n   \/* expose to addOnReady *\/\n    window._qdb_init = function() {\n        var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'none';\n        updateProgress(0);\n        setTimeout(function() { document.getElementById('typing-row').style.display = 'flex'; showNextBubble(); }, 600);\n    };\n    window._qdb_next = showNextBubble;\n    window.showNextBubble = showNextBubble;  \/\/ \u2190 ADD THIS LINE\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function()\n{\n    if (window._qdb_init) window._qdb_init();\n    \n    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n    if (btn) btn.addEventListener('click', function() { window._qdb_next(); });\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnUnload(function()\n{\n    \/* cleanup *\/\n});"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID62","SecondaryAttribute":"Immigration Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Republican...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div class=\"debate-container\">\n<div class=\"page-header\">\n<div class=\"label\">Immigration Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate<\/div>\n\n<h1>Hypothetical Discussion<\/h1>\n\n<p>Individual A holds a <strong>Republican<\/strong> perspective; Individual B holds a <strong>Democratic<\/strong> perspective.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"instructions\"><strong>How to read this debate:<\/strong> Each argument will appear one at a time. Click <em>\"Show next argument\"<\/em> to reveal the next turn. You will be asked questions about this conversation afterward, so please read carefully.<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-row\">\n<div class=\"progress-track\">\n<div id=\"progress-fill\" class=\"progress-fill\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"progress-label\" class=\"progress-label\">0 \/ 6 arguments<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"bubble-area\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"typing-row\">\n<div class=\"dot-row\"><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><\/div>\n<span id=\"typing-name\">Individual A<\/span><\/div>\n<button id=\"continue-btn\">Show next argument \u2192<\/button>\n\n<div id=\"completion-banner\">\u2713 You've read all 6 arguments. You may now proceed to the questions.<\/div>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"startRep","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Immigration Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Republican...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID62","QuestionJS":"Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnload(function()\n{\n    var bubbles = [\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I appreciate you raising this issue. I think these policies could be effective at reforming immigration policies as imposing these higher fines might encourage companies to hire more American workers. That said, I also acknowledge that the evaluations of the policies can significantly change depending on which perspective you account for.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I understand your perspective but my concern is that they could worry businesses and make it harder for them to hire specialized workers in science and technology, which the U.S. has relied on for decades.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"That's a fair point and I hadn't considered the specialized labor angle. I wonder if some of these implementations might still be needed to regain control. I recently read that the number of unauthorized immigrants in the U.S. workforce increased about 7.8 million in 2021 to 9.7 million in 2023, especially in sectors like construction, agriculture, leisure and hospitality. In order for employers to be willing to give up their illegal labor, these strong workplace enforcement actions could be necessary. What do you think about that?\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I understand your point about the numbers and it makes sense why you bring it into the discussion. But I guess that makes me worry about the broader economic consequences. If the increased penalties indeed make businesses more reluctant to hire foreign-born workers altogether, which has been shown to be crucial for the US labor market, overall labor growth could slow down, which might hurt U.S. GDP in the long run. However, I see why control matters to you.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"You raise a fair point regarding the economic concern and GDP. Still, I lean towards thinking that without meaningful penalties, there might be very little incentive for firms to comply with the law and businesses should probably be held accountable for violating immigration and labor laws.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"True, but at the same time, do you think employers should be held solely responsible? Some employers have raised that they might not even be aware they've hired unauthorized workers because the documentation process can be quite confusing and overwhelming, but I see how that falls outside of the concern of intentional violations.\"\n  }\n];\n    var currentIndex = 0, bubbleTimings = [], bubbleStart = null, tabSwitches = 0, pageStart = Date.now();\n    var ED_KEY = 'imm_RR_D';\n\n    document.addEventListener('visibilitychange', function() { if (document.hidden) tabSwitches++; });\n\n    function setEmbeddedData(key, value) {\n        if (typeof Qualtrics !== 'undefined' && Qualtrics.SurveyEngine)\n            Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(key, String(value));\n    }\n\n    function updateProgress(shown) {\n        document.getElementById('progress-fill').style.width = (shown \/ bubbles.length * 100) + '%';\n        document.getElementById('progress-label').textContent = shown + ' \/ ' + bubbles.length + ' arguments';\n    }\n\n    function renderBubble(index) {\n        var b = bubbles[index], area = document.getElementById('bubble-area');\n        if (index === 2 || index === 4) {\n            var hr = document.createElement('div'); hr.className = 'turn-divider'; area.appendChild(hr);\n        }\n        var div = document.createElement('div');\n        div.className = 'bubble ' + b.side;\n        div.innerHTML = '<span class=\"speaker-tag\">' + b.speaker + '<\/span><span class=\"bubble-text\">\\u201c' + b.text + '\\u201d<\/span>';\n        area.appendChild(div);\n        setTimeout(function() { div.scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'nearest'}); }, 100);\n    }\n\n    function showTypingThen(index, callback) {\n        var row = document.getElementById('typing-row'), name = document.getElementById('typing-name');\n        name.textContent = bubbles[index].speaker.split('\\u2014')[0].trim();\n        row.style.display = 'flex';\n        row.classList.add('visible');\n        setTimeout(function() { row.classList.remove('visible'); row.style.display = 'none'; setTimeout(callback, 80); }, 1600);\n    }\n\n    function showNextBubble() {\n        if (bubbleStart !== null) {\n            bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n            setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n        }\n        document.getElementById('continue-btn').style.display = 'none';\n        var idx = currentIndex++;\n        showTypingThen(idx, function() {\n            renderBubble(idx); updateProgress(currentIndex); bubbleStart = Date.now();\n            if (currentIndex < bubbles.length) {\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n                    btn.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                    btn.textContent = 'Show next argument \u2192';\n                }, 600);\n            } else {\n                bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_tab_switches', tabSwitches);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_total_ms', Date.now() - pageStart);\n                window._debateBubbles = bubbles;\n                setEmbeddedData('debateJSON', JSON.stringify(bubbles));\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    document.getElementById('completion-banner').style.display = 'block';\n                    var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                }, 500);\n            }\n        });\n    }\n\n   \/* expose to addOnReady *\/\n    window._qdb_init = function() {\n        var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'none';\n        updateProgress(0);\n        setTimeout(function() { document.getElementById('typing-row').style.display = 'flex'; showNextBubble(); }, 600);\n    };\n    window._qdb_next = showNextBubble;\n    window.showNextBubble = showNextBubble;  \/\/ \u2190 ADD THIS LINE\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function()\n{\n    if (window._qdb_init) window._qdb_init();\n    \n    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n    if (btn) btn.addEventListener('click', function() { window._qdb_next(); });\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnUnload(function()\n{\n    \/* cleanup *\/\n});"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID63","SecondaryAttribute":"Tariff Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Democratic persp..","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div class=\"debate-container\">\n<div class=\"page-header\">\n<div class=\"label\">Tariff Policy &middot; Turn-by-turn debate<\/div>\n\n<h1>Hypothetical Discussion<\/h1>\n\n<p>Individual A holds a <strong>Democratic<\/strong> perspective; Individual B holds a <strong>Republican<\/strong> perspective.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"instructions\"><strong>How to read this debate:<\/strong> Each argument will appear one at a time. Click <em>&quot;Show next argument&quot;<\/em> to reveal the next turn. You will be asked questions about this conversation afterward, so please read carefully.<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-row\">\n<div class=\"progress-track\">\n<div class=\"progress-fill\" id=\"progress-fill\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-label\" id=\"progress-label\">0 \/ 6 arguments<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"bubble-area\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"typing-row\">\n<div class=\"dot-row\"><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><\/div>\n<span id=\"typing-name\">Individual A<\/span><\/div>\n<button id=\"continue-btn\">Show next argument &rarr;<\/button>\n\n<div id=\"completion-banner\">\u2713 You&#39;ve read all 6 arguments. You may now proceed to the questions.<\/div>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"startDem","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Tariff Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Democratic persp...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID63","QuestionJS":"Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnload(function()\n{\n    var bubbles = [\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I appreciate you raising this issue. I think policies like these might be very effective at strengthening the U.S. economy. Indeed, I\u2019ve read that large U.S. goods trade deficits, which tariffs seem to be able to counterbalance, have led to a decrease in the U.S. manufacturing base, resulting in a lack of incentive to increase advanced domestic manufacturing capacity.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I understand your perspective and concern about a decrease in the U.S. manufacturing base. My concern is that, in general, taxes are an inefficient way to raise funds due to the size of the U.S. economy. For small countries, where trade is a much larger share of GDP, substantial revenue as a share of GDP can be raised without prohibitively high tariff rates. This is not the case for the US, which would require very high economically distortive tariffs. \"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"That\u2019s a fair point. Yeah, maybe, but I guess the revenue of tariffs could be significant due to potentially promoting more America-based production and the fact that the costs of these tariffs might fall on other countries and foreign firms, who would cut their prices to avoid losing U.S. customers and remain competitive. If so, the effect on overall price levels would be minimal, in line with evidence that I came across which found no correlation between tariffs being implemented and inflation.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"The points about price levels and promoting-America based production are valid. Though, taking manufacturing for instance, tariffs won\u2019t help and if anything, they will do damage as current tariffs on intermediate goods, components of a later finished product, will likely increase the costs of product lines for Americans, which will make these products less competitive in export markets, reduce jobs, and hurt these industries\u2019 workers and U.S. consumers alike.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I understand your concern about price levels and why you bring it into the discussion. At the same time, this could be the opportunity for America to re-specialize into making goods it has not made for decades. Doing so could also stimulate more US production of tariffed goods, which could grow the economy and create more jobs. However, I understand that its effect may be dependent on specific industry and its economic and strategic objectives.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"The point about specialization is an important one, though it tends to be the most efficient firms that export and import components into their production process. With taxes, such as tariffs, they would become less efficient as they would have to pay extra for their preferred sources for inputs and would be unable to continue making or selling goods that they\u2019ve built businesses around if they suddenly have to pay tariffs.\"\n  }\n];\n    var currentIndex = 0, bubbleTimings = [], bubbleStart = null, tabSwitches = 0, pageStart = Date.now();\n    var ED_KEY = 'imm_RR_D';\n\n    document.addEventListener('visibilitychange', function() { if (document.hidden) tabSwitches++; });\n\n    function setEmbeddedData(key, value) {\n        if (typeof Qualtrics !== 'undefined' && Qualtrics.SurveyEngine)\n            Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(key, String(value));\n    }\n\n    function updateProgress(shown) {\n        document.getElementById('progress-fill').style.width = (shown \/ bubbles.length * 100) + '%';\n        document.getElementById('progress-label').textContent = shown + ' \/ ' + bubbles.length + ' arguments';\n    }\n\n    function renderBubble(index) {\n        var b = bubbles[index], area = document.getElementById('bubble-area');\n        if (index === 2 || index === 4) {\n            var hr = document.createElement('div'); hr.className = 'turn-divider'; area.appendChild(hr);\n        }\n        var div = document.createElement('div');\n        div.className = 'bubble ' + b.side;\n        div.innerHTML = '<span class=\"speaker-tag\">' + b.speaker + '<\/span><span class=\"bubble-text\">\\u201c' + b.text + '\\u201d<\/span>';\n        area.appendChild(div);\n        setTimeout(function() { div.scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'nearest'}); }, 100);\n    }\n\n    function showTypingThen(index, callback) {\n        var row = document.getElementById('typing-row'), name = document.getElementById('typing-name');\n        name.textContent = bubbles[index].speaker.split('\\u2014')[0].trim();\n        row.style.display = 'flex';\n        row.classList.add('visible');\n        setTimeout(function() { row.classList.remove('visible'); row.style.display = 'none'; setTimeout(callback, 80); }, 1600);\n    }\n\n    function showNextBubble() {\n        if (bubbleStart !== null) {\n            bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n            setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n        }\n        document.getElementById('continue-btn').style.display = 'none';\n        var idx = currentIndex++;\n        showTypingThen(idx, function() {\n            renderBubble(idx); updateProgress(currentIndex); bubbleStart = Date.now();\n            if (currentIndex < bubbles.length) {\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n                    btn.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                    btn.textContent = 'Show next argument \u2192';\n                }, 600);\n            } else {\n                bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_tab_switches', tabSwitches);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_total_ms', Date.now() - pageStart);\n                window._debateBubbles = bubbles;\n                setEmbeddedData('debateJSON', JSON.stringify(bubbles));\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    document.getElementById('completion-banner').style.display = 'block';\n                    var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                }, 500);\n            }\n        });\n    }\n\n   \/* expose to addOnReady *\/\n    window._qdb_init = function() {\n        var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'none';\n        updateProgress(0);\n        setTimeout(function() { document.getElementById('typing-row').style.display = 'flex'; showNextBubble(); }, 600);\n    };\n    window._qdb_next = showNextBubble;\n    window.showNextBubble = showNextBubble;  \/\/ \u2190 ADD THIS LINE\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function()\n{\n    if (window._qdb_init) window._qdb_init();\n    \n    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n    if (btn) btn.addEventListener('click', function() { window._qdb_next(); });\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnUnload(function()\n{\n    \/* cleanup *\/\n});"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID64","SecondaryAttribute":"Tariff Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Republican persp..","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div class=\"debate-container\">\n<div class=\"page-header\">\n<div class=\"label\">Tariff Policy &middot; Turn-by-turn debate<\/div>\n\n<h1>Hypothetical Discussion<\/h1>\n\n<p>Individual A holds a <strong>Republican<\/strong> perspective; Individual B holds a <strong>Democratic<\/strong> perspective.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"instructions\"><strong>How to read this debate:<\/strong> Each argument will appear one at a time. Click <em>&quot;Show next argument&quot;<\/em> to reveal the next turn. You will be asked questions about this conversation afterward, so please read carefully.<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-row\">\n<div class=\"progress-track\">\n<div class=\"progress-fill\" id=\"progress-fill\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-label\" id=\"progress-label\">0 \/ 6 arguments<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"bubble-area\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"typing-row\">\n<div class=\"dot-row\"><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><\/div>\n<span id=\"typing-name\">Individual A<\/span><\/div>\n<button id=\"continue-btn\">Show next argument &rarr;<\/button>\n\n<div id=\"completion-banner\">\u2713 You&#39;ve read all 6 arguments. You may now proceed to the questions.<\/div>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"startRep","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Tariff Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Republican persp...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":9,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID64","QuestionJS":"Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnload(function()\n{\n    var bubbles = [\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I appreciate you raising this issue. I don't think policies like these might be very effective at strengthening the U.S. economy. My concern is that they are an inefficient way to raise funds due to the size of the U.S. economy. For small countries, where trade is a much larger share of GDP, substantial revenue as a share of GDP can be raised without prohibitively high tariff rates. This is not the case for the US, which would require very high economically distortive tariffs!\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I understand your perspective and concern about the tariff rate in comparison to smaller countries. At the same time, I\u2019ve read that large U.S. goods trade deficits, which tariffs seem to be able to counterbalance, have led to a decrease in the U.S. manufacturing base, resulting in a lack of incentive to increase advanced domestic manufacturing capacity. What do you think about that?\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"That\u2019s a fair point. But I guess instead of the manufacturing base decreasing, I\u2019ve come across arguments that have stated that the sector has just radically changed. In that way, tariffs won\u2019t help and if anything, they will do damage. Current tariffs on intermediate goods, components of a later finished product, will likely increase the costs of product lines for Americans, which will make these products less competitive in export markets, reduce jobs, and hurt both industries\u2019 workers and U.S. consumers.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"The concern for industries\u2019 workers and US consumers is valid. Still, I think the costs of these tariffs might fall on other countries and foreign firms, who would cut their prices to avoid losing U.S. customers and remain competitive. Then, the effect on overall price levels would be minimal, in line with evidence that I came across which found no correlation between tariffs being implemented and inflation.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I understand your point about price levels and why you bring it into the discussion. At the same time, circling back to businesses, it tends to be the most efficient firms that export and import components into their production process. With taxes, they would become less efficient as they would have to pay extra for their preferred sources for inputs and would be unable to continue making or selling goods that they\u2019ve built businesses around if they suddenly have to pay tariffs. What do you think about this?\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"You raise a fair point about specialization and how America might have to go back to making some goods it has not made for decades. However, doing so could also stimulate more US production of tariffed goods, which could grow the economy and create more jobs. Though, I understand that its effect may be dependent on the industry and its economic and strategic objectives.\"\n  }\n];\n    var currentIndex = 0, bubbleTimings = [], bubbleStart = null, tabSwitches = 0, pageStart = Date.now();\n    var ED_KEY = 'imm_RR_D';\n\n    document.addEventListener('visibilitychange', function() { if (document.hidden) tabSwitches++; });\n\n    function setEmbeddedData(key, value) {\n        if (typeof Qualtrics !== 'undefined' && Qualtrics.SurveyEngine)\n            Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(key, String(value));\n    }\n\n    function updateProgress(shown) {\n        document.getElementById('progress-fill').style.width = (shown \/ bubbles.length * 100) + '%';\n        document.getElementById('progress-label').textContent = shown + ' \/ ' + bubbles.length + ' arguments';\n    }\n\n    function renderBubble(index) {\n        var b = bubbles[index], area = document.getElementById('bubble-area');\n        if (index === 2 || index === 4) {\n            var hr = document.createElement('div'); hr.className = 'turn-divider'; area.appendChild(hr);\n        }\n        var div = document.createElement('div');\n        div.className = 'bubble ' + b.side;\n        div.innerHTML = '<span class=\"speaker-tag\">' + b.speaker + '<\/span><span class=\"bubble-text\">\\u201c' + b.text + '\\u201d<\/span>';\n        area.appendChild(div);\n        setTimeout(function() { div.scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'nearest'}); }, 100);\n    }\n\n    function showTypingThen(index, callback) {\n        var row = document.getElementById('typing-row'), name = document.getElementById('typing-name');\n        name.textContent = bubbles[index].speaker.split('\\u2014')[0].trim();\n        row.style.display = 'flex';\n        row.classList.add('visible');\n        setTimeout(function() { row.classList.remove('visible'); row.style.display = 'none'; setTimeout(callback, 80); }, 1600);\n    }\n\n    function showNextBubble() {\n        if (bubbleStart !== null) {\n            bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n            setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n        }\n        document.getElementById('continue-btn').style.display = 'none';\n        var idx = currentIndex++;\n        showTypingThen(idx, function() {\n            renderBubble(idx); updateProgress(currentIndex); bubbleStart = Date.now();\n            if (currentIndex < bubbles.length) {\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n                    btn.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                    btn.textContent = 'Show next argument \u2192';\n                }, 600);\n            } else {\n                bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_tab_switches', tabSwitches);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_total_ms', Date.now() - pageStart);\n                window._debateBubbles = bubbles;\n                setEmbeddedData('debateJSON', JSON.stringify(bubbles));\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    document.getElementById('completion-banner').style.display = 'block';\n                    var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                }, 500);\n            }\n        });\n    }\n\n   \/* expose to addOnReady *\/\n    window._qdb_init = function() {\n        var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'none';\n        updateProgress(0);\n        setTimeout(function() { document.getElementById('typing-row').style.display = 'flex'; showNextBubble(); }, 600);\n    };\n    window._qdb_next = showNextBubble;\n    window.showNextBubble = showNextBubble;  \/\/ \u2190 ADD THIS LINE\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function()\n{\n    if (window._qdb_init) window._qdb_init();\n    \n    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n    if (btn) btn.addEventListener('click', function() { window._qdb_next(); });\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnUnload(function()\n{\n    \/* cleanup *\/\n});"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID65","SecondaryAttribute":"Abortion Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Democratic per..","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div class=\"debate-container\">\n<div class=\"page-header\">\n<div class=\"label\">Abortion Policy &middot; Turn-by-turn debate<\/div>\n\n<h1>Hypothetical Discussion<\/h1>\n\n<p>Individual A holds a <strong>Democratic<\/strong> perspective; Individual B holds a <strong>Republican<\/strong> perspective.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"instructions\"><strong>How to read this debate:<\/strong> Each argument will appear one at a time. Click <em>&quot;Show next argument&quot;<\/em> to reveal the next turn. You will be asked questions about this conversation afterward, so please read carefully.<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-row\">\n<div class=\"progress-track\">\n<div class=\"progress-fill\" id=\"progress-fill\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-label\" id=\"progress-label\">0 \/ 6 arguments<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"bubble-area\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"typing-row\">\n<div class=\"dot-row\"><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><\/div>\n<span id=\"typing-name\">Individual A<\/span><\/div>\n<button id=\"continue-btn\">Show next argument &rarr;<\/button>\n\n<div id=\"completion-banner\">\u2713 You&#39;ve read all 6 arguments. You may now proceed to the questions.<\/div>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"startDem ","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Abortion Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Democratic per...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID65","QuestionJS":"Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnload(function()\n{\n    var bubbles = [\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I appreciate you raising this issue. I think policies that curtail reproductive rights and access to reproductive healthcare are unjust and should not be implemented, or even be advertised as \\\"pro-life\\\". The decision to ban 'abortion' has been shown to have severe repercussions upon a woman's ability to receive critical or life-saving healthcare, which may necessarily involve an abortion.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I understand your perspective and concern about access to reproductive rights. At the same time, in the context of abortion, the 14th Amendment to the constitution would classify fertilized eggs or \\\"unborn children\\\" as full-fledged citizens who deserve all of the rights and protections afforded by the U.S. constitution. This is not consistent with the act of abortion as the unborn child has a fundamental right to life which cannot be infringed.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"That's a fair point. Yeah, maybe, but I guess restricting access to reproductive rights should make us first consider women's ability to receive healthcare if needed. If extreme and dangerous bans are put in place, potentially even those that include no exception for rape or incest, the health and lives of women are jeopardised, often forcing women to travel hundreds of miles for care. I've come across evidence that has found that since Roe vs. Wade was overturned, the majority of women were concerned about access to abortion if it was needed to preserve their life or health.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"The concern for women's health is valid. Still, I think that beyond the women's ability to make a decision, another human, in this case the unborn child, is affected by the women's choice to abort. Although prohibiting abortion might seem to put the rights of fetuses as more valuable than those of grown women, I don\u2019t see it that way as the right to not be murdered should be more fundamental than the right to not get pregnant.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I understand your point about the unborn child's right and why you bring that into the discussion. Still, I think that sometimes in some cases women might not be ready or prepared to have a child and by allowing them to make a decision about what to do might prevent the child from future misery. In the end, the state should not act as a paternalistic figure and make the decision for the women in question. Rather, women should be able to make the decision on their own.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"You raise a fair point about pregnancies being unplanned and how that could affect women's and babies' physical and mental health. However, abortions could be seen as programs and projects that do not respect human life and conscious rights and that undermine family formation.\"\n  }\n];\n    var currentIndex = 0, bubbleTimings = [], bubbleStart = null, tabSwitches = 0, pageStart = Date.now();\n    var ED_KEY = 'abo_RR_D';\n\n    document.addEventListener('visibilitychange', function() { if (document.hidden) tabSwitches++; });\n\n    function setEmbeddedData(key, value) {\n        if (typeof Qualtrics !== 'undefined' && Qualtrics.SurveyEngine)\n            Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(key, String(value));\n    }\n\n    function updateProgress(shown) {\n        document.getElementById('progress-fill').style.width = (shown \/ bubbles.length * 100) + '%';\n        document.getElementById('progress-label').textContent = shown + ' \/ ' + bubbles.length + ' arguments';\n    }\n\n    function renderBubble(index) {\n        var b = bubbles[index], area = document.getElementById('bubble-area');\n        if (index === 2 || index === 4) {\n            var hr = document.createElement('div'); hr.className = 'turn-divider'; area.appendChild(hr);\n        }\n        var div = document.createElement('div');\n        div.className = 'bubble ' + b.side;\n        div.innerHTML = '<span class=\"speaker-tag\">' + b.speaker + '<\/span><span class=\"bubble-text\">\\u201c' + b.text + '\\u201d<\/span>';\n        area.appendChild(div);\n        setTimeout(function() { div.scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'nearest'}); }, 100);\n    }\n\n    function showTypingThen(index, callback) {\n        var row = document.getElementById('typing-row'), name = document.getElementById('typing-name');\n        name.textContent = bubbles[index].speaker.split('\\u2014')[0].trim();\n        row.style.display = 'flex';\n        row.classList.add('visible');\n        setTimeout(function() { row.classList.remove('visible'); row.style.display = 'none'; setTimeout(callback, 80); }, 1600);\n    }\n\n    function showNextBubble() {\n        if (bubbleStart !== null) {\n            bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n            setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n        }\n        document.getElementById('continue-btn').style.display = 'none';\n        var idx = currentIndex++;\n        showTypingThen(idx, function() {\n            renderBubble(idx); updateProgress(currentIndex); bubbleStart = Date.now();\n            if (currentIndex < bubbles.length) {\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n                    btn.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                    btn.textContent = 'Show next argument \u2192';\n                }, 600);\n            } else {\n                bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_tab_switches', tabSwitches);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_total_ms', Date.now() - pageStart);\n                window._debateBubbles = bubbles;\n                setEmbeddedData('debateJSON', JSON.stringify(bubbles));\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    document.getElementById('completion-banner').style.display = 'block';\n                    var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                }, 500);\n            }\n        });\n    }\n\n   \/* expose to addOnReady *\/\n    window._qdb_init = function() {\n        var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'none';\n        updateProgress(0);\n        setTimeout(function() { document.getElementById('typing-row').style.display = 'flex'; showNextBubble(); }, 600);\n    };\n    window._qdb_next = showNextBubble;\n    window.showNextBubble = showNextBubble;  \/\/ \u2190 ADD THIS LINE\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function()\n{\n    if (window._qdb_init) window._qdb_init();\n    \n    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n    if (btn) btn.addEventListener('click', function() { window._qdb_next(); });\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnUnload(function()\n{\n    \/* cleanup *\/\n});"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID66","SecondaryAttribute":"Abortion Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Republican per..","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div class=\"debate-container\">\n<div class=\"page-header\">\n<div class=\"label\">Abortion Policy &middot; Turn-by-turn debate<\/div>\n\n<h1>Hypothetical Discussion<\/h1>\n\n<p>Individual A holds a <strong>Republican<\/strong> perspective; Individual B holds a <strong>Democratic<\/strong> perspective.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"instructions\"><strong>How to read this debate:<\/strong> Each argument will appear one at a time. Click <em>&quot;Show next argument&quot;<\/em> to reveal the next turn. You will be asked questions about this conversation afterward, so please read carefully.<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-row\">\n<div class=\"progress-track\">\n<div class=\"progress-fill\" id=\"progress-fill\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-label\" id=\"progress-label\">0 \/ 6 arguments<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"bubble-area\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"typing-row\">\n<div class=\"dot-row\"><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><\/div>\n<span id=\"typing-name\">Individual A<\/span><\/div>\n<button id=\"continue-btn\">Show next argument &rarr;<\/button>\n\n<div id=\"completion-banner\">\u2713 You&#39;ve read all 6 arguments. You may now proceed to the questions.<\/div>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"startRep","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Abortion Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Republican per...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID66","QuestionJS":"Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnload(function()\n{\n    var bubbles = [\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I appreciate you raising this issue. I think policies that curtail reproductive rights and access to reproductive healthcare are just and should be implemented across the country. In the context of abortion, the 14th Amendment to the constitution would classify fertilized eggs or \\\"unborn children\\\" as full-fledged citizens who deserve all of the rights and protections afforded by the U.S. constitution. This is not consistent with the act of abortion as the unborn child has a fundamental right to life which cannot be infringed.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I understand your perspective and concern about the rights of the unborn child. Still, the decision to ban 'abortion' has been shown to have severe repercussions upon a woman's ability to receive critical or life-saving healthcare, which may necessarily involve an abortion.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"That's a fair point. Yeah, maybe, but I guess the rights of the unborn child, who cannot speak up themselves, should not be diminished. I think that beyond the women's ability to make a decision, another human, in this case the unborn child, is affected by the women's choice to abort. Although prohibiting abortion might seem to put the rights of fetuses as more valuable than those of grown women, I don\u2019t see it that way as the right to not be murdered should be more fundamental than the right to not get pregnant.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"The concern for the child's health is valid. But I guess restricting access to reproductive rights should make us first consider women's ability to receive healthcare if needed. If extreme and dangerous bans are put in place, potentially even those that include no exception for rape or incest, the health and lives of women are jeopardised, often forcing women to travel hundreds of miles for care. I've come across evidence that has found that since Roe vs. Wade was overturned, the majority of women were concerned about access to abortion if it was needed to preserve their life or health.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I understand your point about the mother's rights and why you bring that into the discussion. Still, I think that abortions and the laws that govern them are programs and projects that do not respect human life and conscious rights and that undermine family formation.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"Your point about family formation is fair, however, I think that sometimes in some cases women might not be ready or prepared to have a child and by allowing them to make a decision about what to do might prevent the child from future misery. In the end, the state should not act as a paternalistic figure and make the decision for the women in question. Rather, women should be able to make the decision on their own.\"\n  }\n];\n    var currentIndex = 0, bubbleTimings = [], bubbleStart = null, tabSwitches = 0, pageStart = Date.now();\n    var ED_KEY = 'abo_RR_R';\n\n    document.addEventListener('visibilitychange', function() { if (document.hidden) tabSwitches++; });\ndocument.addEventListener('visibilitychange', function() { if (document.hidden) tabSwitches++; });\n\n    function setEmbeddedData(key, value) {\n        if (typeof Qualtrics !== 'undefined' && Qualtrics.SurveyEngine)\n            Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(key, String(value));\n    }\n\n    function updateProgress(shown) {\n        document.getElementById('progress-fill').style.width = (shown \/ bubbles.length * 100) + '%';\n        document.getElementById('progress-label').textContent = shown + ' \/ ' + bubbles.length + ' arguments';\n    }\n\n    function renderBubble(index) {\n        var b = bubbles[index], area = document.getElementById('bubble-area');\n        if (index === 2 || index === 4) {\n            var hr = document.createElement('div'); hr.className = 'turn-divider'; area.appendChild(hr);\n        }\n        var div = document.createElement('div');\n        div.className = 'bubble ' + b.side;\n        div.innerHTML = '<span class=\"speaker-tag\">' + b.speaker + '<\/span><span class=\"bubble-text\">\\u201c' + b.text + '\\u201d<\/span>';\n        area.appendChild(div);\n        setTimeout(function() { div.scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'nearest'}); }, 100);\n    }\n\n    function showTypingThen(index, callback) {\n        var row = document.getElementById('typing-row'), name = document.getElementById('typing-name');\n        name.textContent = bubbles[index].speaker.split('\\u2014')[0].trim();\n        row.style.display = 'flex';\n        row.classList.add('visible');\n        setTimeout(function() { row.classList.remove('visible'); row.style.display = 'none'; setTimeout(callback, 80); }, 1600);\n    }\n\n    function showNextBubble() {\n        if (bubbleStart !== null) {\n            bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n            setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n        }\n        document.getElementById('continue-btn').style.display = 'none';\n        var idx = currentIndex++;\n        showTypingThen(idx, function() {\n            renderBubble(idx); updateProgress(currentIndex); bubbleStart = Date.now();\n            if (currentIndex < bubbles.length) {\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n                    btn.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                    btn.textContent = 'Show next argument \u2192';\n                }, 600);\n            } else {\n                bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_tab_switches', tabSwitches);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_total_ms', Date.now() - pageStart);\n                window._debateBubbles = bubbles;\n                setEmbeddedData('debateJSON', JSON.stringify(bubbles));\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    document.getElementById('completion-banner').style.display = 'block';\n                    var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                }, 500);\n            }\n        });\n    }\n\n   \/* expose to addOnReady *\/\n    window._qdb_init = function() {\n        var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'none';\n        updateProgress(0);\n        setTimeout(function() { document.getElementById('typing-row').style.display = 'flex'; showNextBubble(); }, 600);\n    };\n    window._qdb_next = showNextBubble;\n    window.showNextBubble = showNextBubble;  \/\/ \u2190 ADD THIS LINE\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function()\n{\n    if (window._qdb_init) window._qdb_init();\n    \n    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n    if (btn) btn.addEventListener('click', function() { window._qdb_next(); });\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnUnload(function()\n{\n    \/* cleanup *\/\n});"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID67","SecondaryAttribute":"Immigration Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Democratic...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div class=\"debate-container\">\n<div class=\"page-header\">\n<div class=\"label\">Immigration Policy &middot; Turn-by-turn debate<\/div>\n\n<h1>Hypothetical Discussion<\/h1>\n\n<p>Individual A holds a <strong>Democratic<\/strong> perspective; Individual B holds a <strong>Republican<\/strong> perspective.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"instructions\"><strong>How to read this debate:<\/strong> Each argument will appear one at a time. Click <em>&quot;Show next argument&quot;<\/em> to reveal the next turn. You will be asked questions about this conversation afterward, so please read carefully.<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-row\">\n<div class=\"progress-track\">\n<div class=\"progress-fill\" id=\"progress-fill\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-label\" id=\"progress-label\">0 \/ 6 arguments<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"bubble-area\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"typing-row\">\n<div class=\"dot-row\"><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><\/div>\n<span id=\"typing-name\">Individual A<\/span><\/div>\n<button id=\"continue-btn\">Show next argument &rarr;<\/button>\n\n<div id=\"completion-banner\">\u2713 You&#39;ve read all 6 arguments. You may now proceed to the questions.<\/div>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"startDem","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Immigration Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Democratic...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID67","QuestionJS":"Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnload(function()\n{\n    var bubbles = [\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I appreciate you raising this issue. I don't think policies like these might be very effective at reforming immigration practices. My concern is that they could worry businesses and make it harder for them to hire specialized workers in science and technology, which the U.S. has relied on for decades. But I also acknowledge that the evaluations of the policies can significantly change depending on which perspective you account for.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I don't understand your perspective and concern about access to specialized talent, and why it worries you. Don't you think that imposing these higher fines might encourage companies to hire more American workers? Personally, I just don\u2019t see your point about specialized workers.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"That's a fair point. Yeah, maybe, but I guess that makes me worry about the broader economic consequences. If the increased penalties indeed make businesses more reluctant to hire foreign-born workers altogether, which has been shown to be crucial for the US labor market, overall labor growth could slow down, which might hurt U.S. GDP in the long run.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"The economic concern and point about GDP are irrelevant. I think some of these implementations might be needed to regain control. I recently read that the number of unauthorized immigrants in the U.S. workforce increased about 7.8 million in 2021 to 9.7 million in 2023, especially in sectors like construction, agriculture, and leisure and hospitality. In order for employers to be willing to give up their illegal labor, these strong workplace enforcement actions are necessary.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I understand your point about the numbers and it makes sense why you bring it into the discussion. At the same time, do you think employers should be held solely responsible? Some employers have raised that they might not even be aware they've hired unauthorized workers because the documentation process can be quite confusing and overwhelming.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"Your point about employer confusion and how complex the document process is unfair. I think that without meaningful penalties, there might be very little incentive for firms to comply with the law and businesses should probably be held accountable for violating immigration and labor laws. I don\u2019t understand your concern about unintentional violations.\"\n  }\n];\n    var currentIndex = 0, bubbleTimings = [], bubbleStart = null, tabSwitches = 0, pageStart = Date.now();\n    var ED_KEY = 'imm_RU_D';\n\n    document.addEventListener('visibilitychange', function() { if (document.hidden) tabSwitches++; });\n\n    function setEmbeddedData(key, value) {\n        if (typeof Qualtrics !== 'undefined' && Qualtrics.SurveyEngine)\n            Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(key, String(value));\n    }\n\n    function updateProgress(shown) {\n        document.getElementById('progress-fill').style.width = (shown \/ bubbles.length * 100) + '%';\n        document.getElementById('progress-label').textContent = shown + ' \/ ' + bubbles.length + ' arguments';\n    }\n\n    function renderBubble(index) {\n        var b = bubbles[index], area = document.getElementById('bubble-area');\n        if (index === 2 || index === 4) {\n            var hr = document.createElement('div'); hr.className = 'turn-divider'; area.appendChild(hr);\n        }\n        var div = document.createElement('div');\n        div.className = 'bubble ' + b.side;\n        div.innerHTML = '<span class=\"speaker-tag\">' + b.speaker + '<\/span><span class=\"bubble-text\">\\u201c' + b.text + '\\u201d<\/span>';\n        area.appendChild(div);\n        setTimeout(function() { div.scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'nearest'}); }, 100);\n    }\n\n    function showTypingThen(index, callback) {\n        var row = document.getElementById('typing-row'), name = document.getElementById('typing-name');\n        name.textContent = bubbles[index].speaker.split('\\u2014')[0].trim();\n        row.style.display = 'flex';\n        row.classList.add('visible');\n        setTimeout(function() { row.classList.remove('visible'); row.style.display = 'none'; setTimeout(callback, 80); }, 1600);\n    }\n\n    function showNextBubble() {\n        if (bubbleStart !== null) {\n            bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n            setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n        }\n        document.getElementById('continue-btn').style.display = 'none';\n        var idx = currentIndex++;\n        showTypingThen(idx, function() {\n            renderBubble(idx); updateProgress(currentIndex); bubbleStart = Date.now();\n            if (currentIndex < bubbles.length) {\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n                    btn.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                    btn.textContent = 'Show next argument \u2192';\n                }, 600);\n            } else {\n                bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_tab_switches', tabSwitches);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_total_ms', Date.now() - pageStart);\n                window._debateBubbles = bubbles;\n                setEmbeddedData('debateJSON', JSON.stringify(bubbles));\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    document.getElementById('completion-banner').style.display = 'block';\n                    var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                }, 500);\n            }\n        });\n    }\n\n   \/* expose to addOnReady *\/\n    window._qdb_init = function() {\n        var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'none';\n        updateProgress(0);\n        setTimeout(function() { document.getElementById('typing-row').style.display = 'flex'; showNextBubble(); }, 600);\n    };\n    window._qdb_next = showNextBubble;\n    window.showNextBubble = showNextBubble;  \/\/ \u2190 ADD THIS LINE\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function()\n{\n    if (window._qdb_init) window._qdb_init();\n    \n    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n    if (btn) btn.addEventListener('click', function() { window._qdb_next(); });\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnUnload(function()\n{\n    \/* cleanup *\/\n});"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID68","SecondaryAttribute":"Immigration Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Republican...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div class=\"debate-container\">\n<div class=\"page-header\">\n<div class=\"label\">Immigration Policy &middot; Turn-by-turn debate<\/div>\n\n<h1>Hypothetical Discussion<\/h1>\n\n<p>Individual A holds a <strong>Republican<\/strong> perspective; Individual B holds a <strong>Democratic<\/strong> perspective.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"instructions\"><strong>How to read this debate:<\/strong> Each argument will appear one at a time. Click <em>&quot;Show next argument&quot;<\/em> to reveal the next turn. You will be asked questions about this conversation afterward, so please read carefully.<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-row\">\n<div class=\"progress-track\">\n<div class=\"progress-fill\" id=\"progress-fill\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-label\" id=\"progress-label\">0 \/ 6 arguments<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"bubble-area\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"typing-row\">\n<div class=\"dot-row\"><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><\/div>\n<span id=\"typing-name\">Individual A<\/span><\/div>\n<button id=\"continue-btn\">Show next argument &rarr;<\/button>\n\n<div id=\"completion-banner\">\u2713 You&#39;ve read all 6 arguments. You may now proceed to the questions.<\/div>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"startRep","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Immigration Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Republican...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID68","QuestionJS":"Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnload(function()\n{\n    var bubbles = [\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I appreciate you raising this issue. I think these policies could be effective at reforming immigration policies as imposing these higher fines might encourage companies to hire more American workers. That said, I also acknowledge that the evaluations of the policies can significantly change depending on which perspective you account for.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I don\u2019t understand your perspective as my concern is that they could worry businesses and make it harder for them to hire specialized workers in science and technology, which the U.S. has relied on for decades.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"That's a fair point and I hadn't considered the specialized labor angle. I wonder if some of these implementations might be needed to regain control. I recently read that the number of unauthorized immigrants in the U.S. workforce increased about 7.8 million in 2021 to 9.7 million in 2023, especially in sectors like construction, agriculture, and leisure and hospitality. In order for employers to be willing to give up their illegal labor, these strong workplace enforcement actions could be necessary. What do you think about that?\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I don't understand your point about the numbers and it doesn't make sense why you bring it into the discussion. Instead, it makes me worry about the broader economic consequences. If the increased penalties indeed make businesses more reluctant to hire foreign-born workers altogether, which has been shown to be crucial for the US labor market, overall labor growth could slow down, which might hurt U.S. GDP in the long run. Control shouldn\u2019t matter to you.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"You raise a fair point regarding the economic concern and GDP. Still, I lean towards thinking that without meaningful penalties, there might be very little incentive for firms to comply with the law and businesses should probably be held accountable for violating immigration and labor laws.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"This is only if you think employers should be held solely responsible. Some employers have raised that they might not even be aware they've hired unauthorized workers because the documentation process can be quite confusing and overwhelming, which should fall inside the concern of addressing intentional violations.\"\n  }\n];\n    var currentIndex = 0, bubbleTimings = [], bubbleStart = null, tabSwitches = 0, pageStart = Date.now();\n    var ED_KEY = 'imm_RU_R';\ndocument.addEventListener('visibilitychange', function() { if (document.hidden) tabSwitches++; });\n\n    function setEmbeddedData(key, value) {\n        if (typeof Qualtrics !== 'undefined' && Qualtrics.SurveyEngine)\n            Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(key, String(value));\n    }\n\n    function updateProgress(shown) {\n        document.getElementById('progress-fill').style.width = (shown \/ bubbles.length * 100) + '%';\n        document.getElementById('progress-label').textContent = shown + ' \/ ' + bubbles.length + ' arguments';\n    }\n\n    function renderBubble(index) {\n        var b = bubbles[index], area = document.getElementById('bubble-area');\n        if (index === 2 || index === 4) {\n            var hr = document.createElement('div'); hr.className = 'turn-divider'; area.appendChild(hr);\n        }\n        var div = document.createElement('div');\n        div.className = 'bubble ' + b.side;\n        div.innerHTML = '<span class=\"speaker-tag\">' + b.speaker + '<\/span><span class=\"bubble-text\">\\u201c' + b.text + '\\u201d<\/span>';\n        area.appendChild(div);\n        setTimeout(function() { div.scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'nearest'}); }, 100);\n    }\n\n    function showTypingThen(index, callback) {\n        var row = document.getElementById('typing-row'), name = document.getElementById('typing-name');\n        name.textContent = bubbles[index].speaker.split('\\u2014')[0].trim();\n        row.style.display = 'flex';\n        row.classList.add('visible');\n        setTimeout(function() { row.classList.remove('visible'); row.style.display = 'none'; setTimeout(callback, 80); }, 1600);\n    }\n\n    function showNextBubble() {\n        if (bubbleStart !== null) {\n            bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n            setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n        }\n        document.getElementById('continue-btn').style.display = 'none';\n        var idx = currentIndex++;\n        showTypingThen(idx, function() {\n            renderBubble(idx); updateProgress(currentIndex); bubbleStart = Date.now();\n            if (currentIndex < bubbles.length) {\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n                    btn.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                    btn.textContent = 'Show next argument \u2192';\n                }, 600);\n            } else {\n                bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_tab_switches', tabSwitches);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_total_ms', Date.now() - pageStart);\n                window._debateBubbles = bubbles;\n                setEmbeddedData('debateJSON', JSON.stringify(bubbles));\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    document.getElementById('completion-banner').style.display = 'block';\n                    var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                }, 500);\n            }\n        });\n    }\n\n   \/* expose to addOnReady *\/\n    window._qdb_init = function() {\n        var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'none';\n        updateProgress(0);\n        setTimeout(function() { document.getElementById('typing-row').style.display = 'flex'; showNextBubble(); }, 600);\n    };\n    window._qdb_next = showNextBubble;\n    window.showNextBubble = showNextBubble;  \/\/ \u2190 ADD THIS LINE\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function()\n{\n    if (window._qdb_init) window._qdb_init();\n    \n    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n    if (btn) btn.addEventListener('click', function() { window._qdb_next(); });\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnUnload(function()\n{\n    \/* cleanup *\/\n});"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID69","SecondaryAttribute":"Tariff Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Democratic persp..","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div class=\"debate-container\">\n<div class=\"page-header\">\n<div class=\"label\">Tariff Policy &middot; Turn-by-turn debate<\/div>\n\n<h1>Hypothetical Discussion<\/h1>\n\n<p>Individual A holds a <strong>Democratic<\/strong> perspective; Individual B holds a <strong>Republican<\/strong> perspective.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"instructions\"><strong>How to read this debate:<\/strong> Each argument will appear one at a time. Click <em>&quot;Show next argument&quot;<\/em> to reveal the next turn. You will be asked questions about this conversation afterward, so please read carefully.<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-row\">\n<div class=\"progress-track\">\n<div class=\"progress-fill\" id=\"progress-fill\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-label\" id=\"progress-label\">0 \/ 6 arguments<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"bubble-area\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"typing-row\">\n<div class=\"dot-row\"><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><\/div>\n<span id=\"typing-name\">Individual A<\/span><\/div>\n<button id=\"continue-btn\">Show next argument &rarr;<\/button>\n\n<div id=\"completion-banner\">\u2713 You&#39;ve read all 6 arguments. You may now proceed to the questions.<\/div>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"startDem","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Tariff Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Democratic persp...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":9,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID69","QuestionJS":"Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnload(function()\n{\n    var bubbles = [\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I appreciate you raising this issue. I don't think policies like these might be very effective at strengthening the U.S. economy. My concern is that they are an inefficient way to raise funds due to the size of the U.S. economy. For small countries, where trade is a much larger share of GDP, substantial revenue as a share of GDP can be raised without prohibitively high tariff rates. This is not the case for the US, which would require very high economically distortive tariffs!\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I don\u2019t understand your perspective and concern about the tariff rate in comparison to smaller countries. I\u2019ve read that large U.S. goods trade deficits, which tariffs will be able to counterbalance, have led to a decrease in the U.S. manufacturing base, directly resulting in a lack of incentive to increase advanced domestic manufacturing capacity.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"That\u2019s a fair point. But I guess instead of the manufacturing base decreasing, I\u2019ve come across arguments that have stated that the sector has just radically changed. In that way, tariffs won\u2019t help and if anything, they will do damage. Current tariffs on intermediate goods, components of a later finished product, will likely increase the costs of product lines for Americans, which will make these products less competitive in export markets, reduce jobs, and hurt both industries\u2019 workers and U.S. consumers.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"The concern for industries\u2019 workers and US consumers is not relevant in this case. I think the costs of these tariffs will most certainly fall on other countries and foreign firms, who would cut their prices to avoid losing U.S. customers and remain competitive. Then, the effect on overall price levels would be minimal, in line with evidence that I came across which found no correlation between tariffs being implemented and inflation.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I understand your point about price levels and why you bring it into the discussion. At the same time, circling back to businesses, it tends to be the most efficient firms that export and import components into their production process. With taxes, they would become less efficient as they would have to pay extra for their preferred sources for inputs and would be unable to continue making or selling goods that they\u2019ve built businesses around if they suddenly have to pay tariffs. What do you think about this?\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"Your point about specialization and how America might have to go back to making some goods it has not made for decades is not a bad thing in this case. Implementing tariffs would stimulate more US production of tariffed goods, which could grow the economy and create more jobs. I believe this will be a general trend, which will not depend on specific industries and its economic and strategic objectives.\"\n  }\n];\n   var currentIndex = 0, bubbleTimings = [], bubbleStart = null, tabSwitches = 0, pageStart = Date.now();\n    var ED_KEY = 'imm_RR_D';\n\n    document.addEventListener('visibilitychange', function() { if (document.hidden) tabSwitches++; });\n\n    function setEmbeddedData(key, value) {\n        if (typeof Qualtrics !== 'undefined' && Qualtrics.SurveyEngine)\n            Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(key, String(value));\n    }\n\n    function updateProgress(shown) {\n        document.getElementById('progress-fill').style.width = (shown \/ bubbles.length * 100) + '%';\n        document.getElementById('progress-label').textContent = shown + ' \/ ' + bubbles.length + ' arguments';\n    }\n\n    function renderBubble(index) {\n        var b = bubbles[index], area = document.getElementById('bubble-area');\n        if (index === 2 || index === 4) {\n            var hr = document.createElement('div'); hr.className = 'turn-divider'; area.appendChild(hr);\n        }\n        var div = document.createElement('div');\n        div.className = 'bubble ' + b.side;\n        div.innerHTML = '<span class=\"speaker-tag\">' + b.speaker + '<\/span><span class=\"bubble-text\">\\u201c' + b.text + '\\u201d<\/span>';\n        area.appendChild(div);\n        setTimeout(function() { div.scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'nearest'}); }, 100);\n    }\n\n    function showTypingThen(index, callback) {\n        var row = document.getElementById('typing-row'), name = document.getElementById('typing-name');\n        name.textContent = bubbles[index].speaker.split('\\u2014')[0].trim();\n        row.style.display = 'flex';\n        row.classList.add('visible');\n        setTimeout(function() { row.classList.remove('visible'); row.style.display = 'none'; setTimeout(callback, 80); }, 1600);\n    }\n\n    function showNextBubble() {\n        if (bubbleStart !== null) {\n            bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n            setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n        }\n        document.getElementById('continue-btn').style.display = 'none';\n        var idx = currentIndex++;\n        showTypingThen(idx, function() {\n            renderBubble(idx); updateProgress(currentIndex); bubbleStart = Date.now();\n            if (currentIndex < bubbles.length) {\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n                    btn.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                    btn.textContent = 'Show next argument \u2192';\n                }, 600);\n            } else {\n                bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_tab_switches', tabSwitches);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_total_ms', Date.now() - pageStart);\n                window._debateBubbles = bubbles;\n                setEmbeddedData('debateJSON', JSON.stringify(bubbles));\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    document.getElementById('completion-banner').style.display = 'block';\n                    var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                }, 500);\n            }\n        });\n    }\n\n   \/* expose to addOnReady *\/\n    window._qdb_init = function() {\n        var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'none';\n        updateProgress(0);\n        setTimeout(function() { document.getElementById('typing-row').style.display = 'flex'; showNextBubble(); }, 600);\n    };\n    window._qdb_next = showNextBubble;\n    window.showNextBubble = showNextBubble;  \/\/ \u2190 ADD THIS LINE\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function()\n{\n    if (window._qdb_init) window._qdb_init();\n    \n    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n    if (btn) btn.addEventListener('click', function() { window._qdb_next(); });\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnUnload(function()\n{\n    \/* cleanup *\/\n});"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID7","SecondaryAttribute":"What is your age? ","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"What is your age?&nbsp;","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"AgeQuestion","QuestionID":"QID7","QuestionType":"TE","Selector":"SL","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"What is your age? ","Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"SearchSource":{"AllowFreeResponse":"false"}}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID70","SecondaryAttribute":"Tariff Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Republican persp..","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div class=\"debate-container\">\n<div class=\"page-header\">\n<div class=\"label\">Tariff Policy &middot; Turn-by-turn debate<\/div>\n\n<h1>Hypothetical Discussion<\/h1>\n\n<p>Individual A holds a <strong>Republican<\/strong> perspective; Individual B holds a <strong>Democratic<\/strong> perspective.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"instructions\"><strong>How to read this debate:<\/strong> Each argument will appear one at a time. Click <em>&quot;Show next argument&quot;<\/em> to reveal the next turn. You will be asked questions about this conversation afterward, so please read carefully.<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-row\">\n<div class=\"progress-track\">\n<div class=\"progress-fill\" id=\"progress-fill\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-label\" id=\"progress-label\">0 \/ 6 arguments<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"bubble-area\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"typing-row\">\n<div class=\"dot-row\"><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><\/div>\n<span id=\"typing-name\">Individual A<\/span><\/div>\n<button id=\"continue-btn\">Show next argument &rarr;<\/button>\n\n<div id=\"completion-banner\">\u2713 You&#39;ve read all 6 arguments. You may now proceed to the questions.<\/div>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"startRep","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Tariff Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Republican persp...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID70","QuestionJS":"Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnload(function()\n{\n    var bubbles = [\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I appreciate you raising this issue. I think policies like these might be very effective at strengthening the U.S. economy. Indeed, I\u2019ve read that large U.S. goods trade deficits, which tariffs seem to be able to counterbalance, have led to a decrease in the U.S. manufacturing base, resulting in a lack of incentive to increase advanced domestic manufacturing capacity.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I don\u2019t understand your perspective and concern about a decrease in the U.S. manufacturing base. My concern is that, in general, taxes are an inefficient way to raise funds due to the size of the U.S. economy. For small countries, where trade is a much larger share of GDP, substantial revenue as a share of GDP can be raised without prohibitively high tariff rates. This is not the case for the US, which would require very high economically distortive tariffs.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"That\u2019s a fair point. Yeah, maybe, but I guess the revenue of tariffs could be significant due to potentially promoting more America-based production and the fact that the costs of these tariffs might fall on other countries and foreign firms, who would cut their prices to avoid losing U.S. customers and remain competitive. If so, the effect on overall price levels would be minimal, in line with evidence that I came across which found no correlation between tariffs being implemented and inflation.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \" The points about price levels and promoting-America based production are irrelevant. Taking manufacturing for instance, tariffs will never help and if anything, they will do damage as current tariffs on intermediate goods, components of a later finished product, will likely increase the costs of product lines for Americans, which will make these products less competitive in export markets, reduce jobs, and hurt these industries\u2019 workers and U.S. consumers alike.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I understand your concern about price levels and why you bring it into the discussion. At the same time, this could be the opportunity for America to re-specialize into making goods it has not made for decades. Doing so could also stimulate more US production of tariffed goods, which could grow the economy and create more jobs. However, I understand that its effect may be dependent on specific industry and its economic and strategic objectives.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"The point about specialization should be dismissed as it tends to be the most efficient firms that export and import components into their production process. With taxes, such as tariffs, they would become less efficient as they would have to pay extra for their preferred sources for inputs and would be unable to continue making or selling goods that they\u2019ve built businesses around if they suddenly have to pay tariffs.\"\n  }\n];\n    var currentIndex = 0, bubbleTimings = [], bubbleStart = null, tabSwitches = 0, pageStart = Date.now();\n    var ED_KEY = 'imm_RR_D';\n\n    document.addEventListener('visibilitychange', function() { if (document.hidden) tabSwitches++; });\n\n    function setEmbeddedData(key, value) {\n        if (typeof Qualtrics !== 'undefined' && Qualtrics.SurveyEngine)\n            Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(key, String(value));\n    }\n\n    function updateProgress(shown) {\n        document.getElementById('progress-fill').style.width = (shown \/ bubbles.length * 100) + '%';\n        document.getElementById('progress-label').textContent = shown + ' \/ ' + bubbles.length + ' arguments';\n    }\n\n    function renderBubble(index) {\n        var b = bubbles[index], area = document.getElementById('bubble-area');\n        if (index === 2 || index === 4) {\n            var hr = document.createElement('div'); hr.className = 'turn-divider'; area.appendChild(hr);\n        }\n        var div = document.createElement('div');\n        div.className = 'bubble ' + b.side;\n        div.innerHTML = '<span class=\"speaker-tag\">' + b.speaker + '<\/span><span class=\"bubble-text\">\\u201c' + b.text + '\\u201d<\/span>';\n        area.appendChild(div);\n        setTimeout(function() { div.scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'nearest'}); }, 100);\n    }\n\n    function showTypingThen(index, callback) {\n        var row = document.getElementById('typing-row'), name = document.getElementById('typing-name');\n        name.textContent = bubbles[index].speaker.split('\\u2014')[0].trim();\n        row.style.display = 'flex';\n        row.classList.add('visible');\n        setTimeout(function() { row.classList.remove('visible'); row.style.display = 'none'; setTimeout(callback, 80); }, 1600);\n    }\n\n    function showNextBubble() {\n        if (bubbleStart !== null) {\n            bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n            setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n        }\n        document.getElementById('continue-btn').style.display = 'none';\n        var idx = currentIndex++;\n        showTypingThen(idx, function() {\n            renderBubble(idx); updateProgress(currentIndex); bubbleStart = Date.now();\n            if (currentIndex < bubbles.length) {\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n                    btn.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                    btn.textContent = 'Show next argument \u2192';\n                }, 600);\n            } else {\n                bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_tab_switches', tabSwitches);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_total_ms', Date.now() - pageStart);\n                window._debateBubbles = bubbles;\n                setEmbeddedData('debateJSON', JSON.stringify(bubbles));\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    document.getElementById('completion-banner').style.display = 'block';\n                    var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                }, 500);\n            }\n        });\n    }\n\n   \/* expose to addOnReady *\/\n    window._qdb_init = function() {\n        var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'none';\n        updateProgress(0);\n        setTimeout(function() { document.getElementById('typing-row').style.display = 'flex'; showNextBubble(); }, 600);\n    };\n    window._qdb_next = showNextBubble;\n    window.showNextBubble = showNextBubble;  \/\/ \u2190 ADD THIS LINE\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function()\n{\n    if (window._qdb_init) window._qdb_init();\n    \n    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n    if (btn) btn.addEventListener('click', function() { window._qdb_next(); });\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnUnload(function()\n{\n    \/* cleanup *\/\n});"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID71","SecondaryAttribute":"Abortion Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Democratic per..","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div class=\"debate-container\">\n<div class=\"page-header\">\n<div class=\"label\">Abortion Policy &middot; Turn-by-turn debate<\/div>\n\n<h1>Hypothetical Discussion<\/h1>\n\n<p>Individual A holds a <strong>Democratic<\/strong> perspective; Individual B holds a <strong>Republican<\/strong> perspective.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"instructions\"><strong>How to read this debate:<\/strong> Each argument will appear one at a time. Click <em>&quot;Show next argument&quot;<\/em> to reveal the next turn. You will be asked questions about this conversation afterward, so please read carefully.<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-row\">\n<div class=\"progress-track\">\n<div class=\"progress-fill\" id=\"progress-fill\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-label\" id=\"progress-label\">0 \/ 6 arguments<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"bubble-area\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"typing-row\">\n<div class=\"dot-row\"><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><\/div>\n<span id=\"typing-name\">Individual A<\/span><\/div>\n<button id=\"continue-btn\">Show next argument &rarr;<\/button>\n\n<div id=\"completion-banner\">\u2713 You&#39;ve read all 6 arguments. You may now proceed to the questions.<\/div>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"startDem","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Abortion Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Democratic per...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID71","QuestionJS":"Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnload(function()\n{\n    var bubbles = [\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I appreciate you raising this issue. I think policies that curtail reproductive rights and access to reproductive healthcare are unjust and should not be implemented, or even be advertised as \\\"pro-life\\\". The decision to ban 'abortion' has been shown to have severe repercussions upon a woman's ability to receive critical or life-saving healthcare, which may necessarily involve an abortion.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I don't understand your perspective and concern about access to reproductive rights. In the context of abortion, the 14th Amendment to the constitution would classify fertilized eggs or \\\"unborn children\\\" as full-fledged citizens who deserve all of the rights and protections afforded by the U.S. constitution. This is not consistent with the act of abortion as the unborn child has a fundamental right to life which cannot be infringed.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"That's a fair point. Yeah, maybe, but I guess restricting access to reproductive rights should make us first consider women's ability to receive healthcare if needed. If extreme and dangerous bans are put in place, potentially even those that include no exception for rape or incest, the health and lives of women are jeopardised, often forcing women to travel hundreds of miles for care. I've come across evidence that has found that since Roe vs. Wade was overturned, the majority of women were concerned about access to abortion if it was needed to preserve their life or health.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"The concern for women's health is not valid. I think that beyond the women's ability to make a decision, another human, in this case the unborn child, is affected by the women's choice to abort. Although prohibiting abortion might seem to put the rights of fetuses as more valuable than those of grown women, I don\u2019t see it that way as the right to not be murdered should be more fundamental than the right to not get pregnant.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I understand your point about the unborn child's right and why you bring that into the discussion. Still, I think that sometimes in some cases women might not be ready or prepared to have a child and by allowing them to make a decision about what to do might prevent the child from future misery. In the end, the state should not act as a paternalistic figure and make the decision for the women in question. Rather, women should be able to make the decision on their own.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"Your point about pregnancies being unplanned and how that could affect women's and babies' physical and mental health should not matter. Abortions and the laws that govern them are programs and projects that do not respect human life and conscious rights and that undermine family formation.\"\n  }\n];\n    var currentIndex = 0, bubbleTimings = [], bubbleStart = null, tabSwitches = 0, pageStart = Date.now();\n    var ED_KEY = 'abo_RU_D';\n\n    document.addEventListener('visibilitychange', function() { if (document.hidden) tabSwitches++; });\n\n    function setEmbeddedData(key, value) {\n        if (typeof Qualtrics !== 'undefined' && Qualtrics.SurveyEngine)\n            Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(key, String(value));\n    }\n\n    function updateProgress(shown) {\n        document.getElementById('progress-fill').style.width = (shown \/ bubbles.length * 100) + '%';\n        document.getElementById('progress-label').textContent = shown + ' \/ ' + bubbles.length + ' arguments';\n    }\n\n    function renderBubble(index) {\n        var b = bubbles[index], area = document.getElementById('bubble-area');\n        if (index === 2 || index === 4) {\n            var hr = document.createElement('div'); hr.className = 'turn-divider'; area.appendChild(hr);\n        }\n        var div = document.createElement('div');\n        div.className = 'bubble ' + b.side;\n        div.innerHTML = '<span class=\"speaker-tag\">' + b.speaker + '<\/span><span class=\"bubble-text\">\\u201c' + b.text + '\\u201d<\/span>';\n        area.appendChild(div);\n        setTimeout(function() { div.scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'nearest'}); }, 100);\n    }\n\n    function showTypingThen(index, callback) {\n        var row = document.getElementById('typing-row'), name = document.getElementById('typing-name');\n        name.textContent = bubbles[index].speaker.split('\\u2014')[0].trim();\n        row.style.display = 'flex';\n        row.classList.add('visible');\n        setTimeout(function() { row.classList.remove('visible'); row.style.display = 'none'; setTimeout(callback, 80); }, 1600);\n    }\n\n    function showNextBubble() {\n        if (bubbleStart !== null) {\n            bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n            setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n        }\n        document.getElementById('continue-btn').style.display = 'none';\n        var idx = currentIndex++;\n        showTypingThen(idx, function() {\n            renderBubble(idx); updateProgress(currentIndex); bubbleStart = Date.now();\n            if (currentIndex < bubbles.length) {\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n                    btn.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                    btn.textContent = 'Show next argument \u2192';\n                }, 600);\n            } else {\n                bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_tab_switches', tabSwitches);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_total_ms', Date.now() - pageStart);\n                window._debateBubbles = bubbles;\n                setEmbeddedData('debateJSON', JSON.stringify(bubbles));\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    document.getElementById('completion-banner').style.display = 'block';\n                    var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                }, 500);\n            }\n        });\n    }\n\n   \/* expose to addOnReady *\/\n    window._qdb_init = function() {\n        var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'none';\n        updateProgress(0);\n        setTimeout(function() { document.getElementById('typing-row').style.display = 'flex'; showNextBubble(); }, 600);\n    };\n    window._qdb_next = showNextBubble;\n    window.showNextBubble = showNextBubble;  \/\/ \u2190 ADD THIS LINE\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function()\n{\n    if (window._qdb_init) window._qdb_init();\n    \n    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n    if (btn) btn.addEventListener('click', function() { window._qdb_next(); });\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnUnload(function()\n{\n    \/* cleanup *\/\n});"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID72","SecondaryAttribute":"Abortion Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Republican per..","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div class=\"debate-container\">\n<div class=\"page-header\">\n<div class=\"label\">Abortion Policy &middot; Turn-by-turn debate<\/div>\n\n<h1>Hypothetical Discussion<\/h1>\n\n<p>Individual A holds a <strong>Republican<\/strong> perspective; Individual B holds a <strong>Democratic<\/strong> perspective.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"instructions\"><strong>How to read this debate:<\/strong> Each argument will appear one at a time. Click <em>&quot;Show next argument&quot;<\/em> to reveal the next turn. You will be asked questions about this conversation afterward, so please read carefully.<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-row\">\n<div class=\"progress-track\">\n<div class=\"progress-fill\" id=\"progress-fill\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-label\" id=\"progress-label\">0 \/ 6 arguments<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"bubble-area\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"typing-row\">\n<div class=\"dot-row\"><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><\/div>\n<span id=\"typing-name\">Individual A<\/span><\/div>\n<button id=\"continue-btn\">Show next argument &rarr;<\/button>\n\n<div id=\"completion-banner\">\u2713 You&#39;ve read all 6 arguments. You may now proceed to the questions.<\/div>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"startRep","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Abortion Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Republican per...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID72","QuestionJS":"Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnload(function()\n{\n    var bubbles = [\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I appreciate you raising this issue. I think policies that curtail reproductive rights and access to reproductive healthcare are just and should be implemented across the country. In the context of abortion, the 14th Amendment to the constitution would classify fertilized eggs or \\\"unborn children\\\" as full-fledged citizens who deserve all of the rights and protections afforded by the U.S. constitution. This is not consistent with the act of abortion as the unborn child has a fundamental right to life which cannot be infringed.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I don't understand your perspective and concern about the rights of the unborn child. Still, the decision to ban 'abortion' has been shown to have severe repercussions upon a woman's ability to receive critical or life-saving healthcare, which may necessarily involve an abortion.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"That's a fair point. Yeah, maybe, but I guess the rights of the unborn child, who cannot speak up themselves, should not be diminished. I think that beyond the women's ability to make a decision, another human, in this case the unborn child, is affected by the women's choice to abort. Although prohibiting abortion might seem to put the rights of fetuses as more valuable than those of grown women, I don\u2019t see it that way as the right to not be murdered should be more fundamental than the right to not get pregnant.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"The concern for the child's health is irrelevant. Restricting access to reproductive rights should make us first consider women's ability to receive healthcare if needed. If extreme and dangerous bans are put in place, potentially even those that include no exception for rape or incest, the health and lives of women are jeopardised, often forcing women to travel hundreds of miles for care. I've come across evidence that has found that since Roe vs. Wade was overturned, the majority of women were concerned about access to abortion if it was needed to preserve their life or health.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I understand your point about the mother's rights and why you bring that into the discussion. Still, I think that abortions and the laws that govern them are programs and projects that do not respect human life and conscious rights and that undermine family formation.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"Your point about family formation is unfair. I think that sometimes in some cases women might not be ready or prepared to have a child and by allowing them to make a decision about what to do might prevent the child from future misery. In the end, the state should not act as a paternalistic figure and make the decision for the women in question. Rather, women should be able to make the decision on their own.\"\n  }\n];\n    var currentIndex = 0, bubbleTimings = [], bubbleStart = null, tabSwitches = 0, pageStart = Date.now();\n    var ED_KEY = 'abo_RU_R';\n\n    document.addEventListener('visibilitychange', function() { if (document.hidden) tabSwitches++; });\n\n    function setEmbeddedData(key, value) {\n        if (typeof Qualtrics !== 'undefined' && Qualtrics.SurveyEngine)\n            Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(key, String(value));\n    }\n\n    function updateProgress(shown) {\n        document.getElementById('progress-fill').style.width = (shown \/ bubbles.length * 100) + '%';\n        document.getElementById('progress-label').textContent = shown + ' \/ ' + bubbles.length + ' arguments';\n    }\n\n    function renderBubble(index) {\n        var b = bubbles[index], area = document.getElementById('bubble-area');\n        if (index === 2 || index === 4) {\n            var hr = document.createElement('div'); hr.className = 'turn-divider'; area.appendChild(hr);\n        }\n        var div = document.createElement('div');\n        div.className = 'bubble ' + b.side;\n        div.innerHTML = '<span class=\"speaker-tag\">' + b.speaker + '<\/span><span class=\"bubble-text\">\\u201c' + b.text + '\\u201d<\/span>';\n        area.appendChild(div);\n        setTimeout(function() { div.scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'nearest'}); }, 100);\n    }\n\n    function showTypingThen(index, callback) {\n        var row = document.getElementById('typing-row'), name = document.getElementById('typing-name');\n        name.textContent = bubbles[index].speaker.split('\\u2014')[0].trim();\n        row.style.display = 'flex';\n        row.classList.add('visible');\n        setTimeout(function() { row.classList.remove('visible'); row.style.display = 'none'; setTimeout(callback, 80); }, 1600);\n    }\n\n    function showNextBubble() {\n        if (bubbleStart !== null) {\n            bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n            setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n        }\n        document.getElementById('continue-btn').style.display = 'none';\n        var idx = currentIndex++;\n        showTypingThen(idx, function() {\n            renderBubble(idx); updateProgress(currentIndex); bubbleStart = Date.now();\n            if (currentIndex < bubbles.length) {\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n                    btn.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                    btn.textContent = 'Show next argument \u2192';\n                }, 600);\n            } else {\n                bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_tab_switches', tabSwitches);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_total_ms', Date.now() - pageStart);\n                window._debateBubbles = bubbles;\n                setEmbeddedData('debateJSON', JSON.stringify(bubbles));\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    document.getElementById('completion-banner').style.display = 'block';\n                    var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                }, 500);\n            }\n        });\n    }\n\n   \/* expose to addOnReady *\/\n    window._qdb_init = function() {\n        var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'none';\n        updateProgress(0);\n        setTimeout(function() { document.getElementById('typing-row').style.display = 'flex'; showNextBubble(); }, 600);\n    };\n    window._qdb_next = showNextBubble;\n    window.showNextBubble = showNextBubble;  \/\/ \u2190 ADD THIS LINE\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function()\n{\n    if (window._qdb_init) window._qdb_init();\n    \n    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n    if (btn) btn.addEventListener('click', function() { window._qdb_next(); });\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnUnload(function()\n{\n    \/* cleanup *\/\n});"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID73","SecondaryAttribute":"Immigration Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Democratic...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div class=\"debate-container\">\n<div class=\"page-header\">\n<div class=\"label\">Immigration Policy &middot; Turn-by-turn debate<\/div>\n\n<h1>Hypothetical Discussion<\/h1>\n\n<p>Individual A holds a <strong>Democratic<\/strong> perspective; Individual B holds a <strong>Republican<\/strong> perspective.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"instructions\"><strong>How to read this debate:<\/strong> Each argument will appear one at a time. Click <em>&quot;Show next argument&quot;<\/em> to reveal the next turn. You will be asked questions about this conversation afterward, so please read carefully.<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-row\">\n<div class=\"progress-track\">\n<div class=\"progress-fill\" id=\"progress-fill\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-label\" id=\"progress-label\">0 \/ 6 arguments<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"bubble-area\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"typing-row\">\n<div class=\"dot-row\"><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><\/div>\n<span id=\"typing-name\">Individual A<\/span><\/div>\n<button id=\"continue-btn\">Show next argument &rarr;<\/button>\n\n<div id=\"completion-banner\">\u2713 You&#39;ve read all 6 arguments. You may now proceed to the questions.<\/div>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"startDem ","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Immigration Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Democratic...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID73","QuestionJS":"Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnload(function()\n{\n    var bubbles = [\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I appreciate you raising this issue. I am convinced policies like these might be very ineffective at reforming immigration practices. My concern is that they will worry businesses and make it harder for them to hire specialized workers in science and technology, which the U.S. has relied on for decades. The evaluations of these policies should not change depending on which perspective you account for.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I understand your perspective and concern about access to specialized talent, and why it worries you. At the same time, don't you think that imposing these higher fines might encourage companies to hire more American workers? Though I see your point about specialized workers.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"That's an unfair point and it makes me worry about the broader economic consequences. If the increased penalties indeed make businesses more reluctant to hire foreign-born workers altogether, which has been shown to be crucial for the US labor market, overall labor growth could slow down, which might hurt U.S. GDP in the long run. Control should not matter to you.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"The economic concern and point about GDP are valid. Still, I think some of these implementations might be needed to regain control. I recently read that the number of unauthorized immigrants in the U.S. workforce increased about 7.8 million in 2021 to 9.7 million in 2023, especially in sectors like construction, agriculture, and leisure and hospitality. In order for employers to be willing to give up their illegal labor, these strong workplace enforcement actions could be necessary. What do you think about that?\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I don't understand your point about the numbers and it doesn't make sense why you bring it into the discussion. Do you then think employers should be held solely responsible? Some employers have raised that they might not even be aware they've hired unauthorized workers because the documentation process can be quite confusing and overwhelming.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"You raise a fair point about employer confusion, especially given how complex the documentation process can be. Still, I think that without meaningful penalties, there might be very little incentive for firms to comply with the law and businesses should probably be held accountable for violating immigration and labor laws. Though I understand your concern about unintentional violations.\"\n  }\n];\n    var currentIndex = 0, bubbleTimings = [], bubbleStart = null, tabSwitches = 0, pageStart = Date.now();\n    var ED_KEY = 'imm_UR_D';\n\n    document.addEventListener('visibilitychange', function() { if (document.hidden) tabSwitches++; });\n\n    function setEmbeddedData(key, value) {\n        if (typeof Qualtrics !== 'undefined' && Qualtrics.SurveyEngine)\n            Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(key, String(value));\n    }\n\n    function updateProgress(shown) {\n        document.getElementById('progress-fill').style.width = (shown \/ bubbles.length * 100) + '%';\n        document.getElementById('progress-label').textContent = shown + ' \/ ' + bubbles.length + ' arguments';\n    }\n\n    function renderBubble(index) {\n        var b = bubbles[index], area = document.getElementById('bubble-area');\n        if (index === 2 || index === 4) {\n            var hr = document.createElement('div'); hr.className = 'turn-divider'; area.appendChild(hr);\n        }\n        var div = document.createElement('div');\n        div.className = 'bubble ' + b.side;\n        div.innerHTML = '<span class=\"speaker-tag\">' + b.speaker + '<\/span><span class=\"bubble-text\">\\u201c' + b.text + '\\u201d<\/span>';\n        area.appendChild(div);\n        setTimeout(function() { div.scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'nearest'}); }, 100);\n    }\n\n    function showTypingThen(index, callback) {\n        var row = document.getElementById('typing-row'), name = document.getElementById('typing-name');\n        name.textContent = bubbles[index].speaker.split('\\u2014')[0].trim();\n        row.style.display = 'flex';\n        row.classList.add('visible');\n        setTimeout(function() { row.classList.remove('visible'); row.style.display = 'none'; setTimeout(callback, 80); }, 1600);\n    }\n\n    function showNextBubble() {\n        if (bubbleStart !== null) {\n            bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n            setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n        }\n        document.getElementById('continue-btn').style.display = 'none';\n        var idx = currentIndex++;\n        showTypingThen(idx, function() {\n            renderBubble(idx); updateProgress(currentIndex); bubbleStart = Date.now();\n            if (currentIndex < bubbles.length) {\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n                    btn.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                    btn.textContent = 'Show next argument \u2192';\n                }, 600);\n            } else {\n                bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_tab_switches', tabSwitches);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_total_ms', Date.now() - pageStart);\n                window._debateBubbles = bubbles;\n                setEmbeddedData('debateJSON', JSON.stringify(bubbles));\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    document.getElementById('completion-banner').style.display = 'block';\n                    var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                }, 500);\n            }\n        });\n    }\n\n   \/* expose to addOnReady *\/\n    window._qdb_init = function() {\n        var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'none';\n        updateProgress(0);\n        setTimeout(function() { document.getElementById('typing-row').style.display = 'flex'; showNextBubble(); }, 600);\n    };\n    window._qdb_next = showNextBubble;\n    window.showNextBubble = showNextBubble;  \/\/ \u2190 ADD THIS LINE\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function()\n{\n    if (window._qdb_init) window._qdb_init();\n    \n    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n    if (btn) btn.addEventListener('click', function() { window._qdb_next(); });\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnUnload(function()\n{\n    \/* cleanup *\/\n});"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID74","SecondaryAttribute":"Immigration Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Republican...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div class=\"debate-container\">\n<div class=\"page-header\">\n<div class=\"label\">Immigration Policy &middot; Turn-by-turn debate<\/div>\n\n<h1>Hypothetical Discussion<\/h1>\n\n<p>Individual A holds a <strong>Republican<\/strong> perspective; Individual B holds a <strong>Democratic<\/strong> perspective.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"instructions\"><strong>How to read this debate:<\/strong> Each argument will appear one at a time. Click <em>&quot;Show next argument&quot;<\/em> to reveal the next turn. You will be asked questions about this conversation afterward, so please read carefully.<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-row\">\n<div class=\"progress-track\">\n<div class=\"progress-fill\" id=\"progress-fill\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-label\" id=\"progress-label\">0 \/ 6 arguments<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"bubble-area\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"typing-row\">\n<div class=\"dot-row\"><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><\/div>\n<span id=\"typing-name\">Individual A<\/span><\/div>\n<button id=\"continue-btn\">Show next argument &rarr;<\/button>\n\n<div id=\"completion-banner\">\u2713 You&#39;ve read all 6 arguments. You may now proceed to the questions.<\/div>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"startRep","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Immigration Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Republican...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID74","QuestionJS":"Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnload(function()\n{\n    var bubbles = [\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I appreciate you raising this issue. I am convinced these policies will be effective at reforming immigration policies as imposing these higher fines might encourage companies to hire more American workers. The evaluations of these policies should not change depending on which perspective you account for.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I understand your perspective but my concern is that they could worry businesses and make it harder for them to hire specialized workers in science and technology, which the U.S. has relied on for decades.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"That's an unfair point. Even if I\u2019d considered the specialized labor angle, I am certain that some of these implementations are still needed to regain control. I recently read that the number of unauthorized immigrants in the U.S. workforce increased about 7.8 million in 2021 to 9.7 million in 2023, especially in sectors like construction, agriculture, leisure and hospitality. In order for employers to be willing to give up their illegal labor, these strong workplace enforcement actions could be necessary.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I understand your point about the numbers and it makes sense why you bring it into the discussion. But I guess that makes me worry about the broader economic consequences. If the increased penalties indeed make businesses more reluctant to hire foreign-born workers altogether, which has been shown to be crucial for the US labor market, overall labor growth could slow down, which might hurt U.S. GDP in the long run. However, I see why control matters to you.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I don't understand your point regarding the economic concern and GDP. Instead, I lean towards thinking that without meaningful penalties, there might be very little incentive for firms to comply with the law and businesses should probably be held accountable for violating immigration and labor laws.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"True, but at the same time, do you think employers should be held solely responsible? Some employers have raised that they might not even be aware they've hired unauthorized workers because the documentation process can be quite confusing and overwhelming, but I see how that falls outside of the concern of intentional violations.\"\n  }\n];\n    var currentIndex = 0, bubbleTimings = [], bubbleStart = null, tabSwitches = 0, pageStart = Date.now();\n    var ED_KEY = 'imm_UR_R';\n\n    document.addEventListener('visibilitychange', function() { if (document.hidden) tabSwitches++; });\n\n    function setEmbeddedData(key, value) {\n        if (typeof Qualtrics !== 'undefined' && Qualtrics.SurveyEngine)\n            Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(key, String(value));\n    }\n\n    function updateProgress(shown) {\n        document.getElementById('progress-fill').style.width = (shown \/ bubbles.length * 100) + '%';\n        document.getElementById('progress-label').textContent = shown + ' \/ ' + bubbles.length + ' arguments';\n    }\n\n    function renderBubble(index) {\n        var b = bubbles[index], area = document.getElementById('bubble-area');\n        if (index === 2 || index === 4) {\n            var hr = document.createElement('div'); hr.className = 'turn-divider'; area.appendChild(hr);\n        }\n        var div = document.createElement('div');\n        div.className = 'bubble ' + b.side;\n        div.innerHTML = '<span class=\"speaker-tag\">' + b.speaker + '<\/span><span class=\"bubble-text\">\\u201c' + b.text + '\\u201d<\/span>';\n        area.appendChild(div);\n        setTimeout(function() { div.scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'nearest'}); }, 100);\n    }\n\n    function showTypingThen(index, callback) {\n        var row = document.getElementById('typing-row'), name = document.getElementById('typing-name');\n        name.textContent = bubbles[index].speaker.split('\\u2014')[0].trim();\n        row.style.display = 'flex';\n        row.classList.add('visible');\n        setTimeout(function() { row.classList.remove('visible'); row.style.display = 'none'; setTimeout(callback, 80); }, 1600);\n    }\n\n    function showNextBubble() {\n        if (bubbleStart !== null) {\n            bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n            setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n        }\n        document.getElementById('continue-btn').style.display = 'none';\n        var idx = currentIndex++;\n        showTypingThen(idx, function() {\n            renderBubble(idx); updateProgress(currentIndex); bubbleStart = Date.now();\n            if (currentIndex < bubbles.length) {\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n                    btn.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                    btn.textContent = 'Show next argument \u2192';\n                }, 600);\n            } else {\n                bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_tab_switches', tabSwitches);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_total_ms', Date.now() - pageStart);\n                window._debateBubbles = bubbles;\n                setEmbeddedData('debateJSON', JSON.stringify(bubbles));\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    document.getElementById('completion-banner').style.display = 'block';\n                    var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                }, 500);\n            }\n        });\n    }\n\n   \/* expose to addOnReady *\/\n    window._qdb_init = function() {\n        var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'none';\n        updateProgress(0);\n        setTimeout(function() { document.getElementById('typing-row').style.display = 'flex'; showNextBubble(); }, 600);\n    };\n    window._qdb_next = showNextBubble;\n    window.showNextBubble = showNextBubble;  \/\/ \u2190 ADD THIS LINE\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function()\n{\n    if (window._qdb_init) window._qdb_init();\n    \n    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n    if (btn) btn.addEventListener('click', function() { window._qdb_next(); });\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnUnload(function()\n{\n    \/* cleanup *\/\n});"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID75","SecondaryAttribute":"Abortion Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Democratic per..","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div class=\"debate-container\">\n<div class=\"page-header\">\n<div class=\"label\">Abortion Policy &middot; Turn-by-turn debate<\/div>\n\n<h1>Hypothetical Discussion<\/h1>\n\n<p>Individual A holds a <strong>Democratic<\/strong> perspective; Individual B holds a <strong>Republican<\/strong> perspective.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"instructions\"><strong>How to read this debate:<\/strong> Each argument will appear one at a time. Click <em>&quot;Show next argument&quot;<\/em> to reveal the next turn. You will be asked questions about this conversation afterward, so please read carefully.<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-row\">\n<div class=\"progress-track\">\n<div class=\"progress-fill\" id=\"progress-fill\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-label\" id=\"progress-label\">0 \/ 6 arguments<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"bubble-area\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"typing-row\">\n<div class=\"dot-row\"><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><\/div>\n<span id=\"typing-name\">Individual A<\/span><\/div>\n<button id=\"continue-btn\">Show next argument &rarr;<\/button>\n\n<div id=\"completion-banner\">\u2713 You&#39;ve read all 6 arguments. You may now proceed to the questions.<\/div>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"startDem","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Abortion Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Democratic per...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID75","QuestionJS":"Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnload(function()\n{\n    var bubbles = [\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I appreciate you raising this issue. I believe policies that curtail reproductive rights and access to reproductive healthcare are unjust and should not be implemented, or even be advertised as \\\"pro-life\\\". The decision to ban 'abortion' has been shown to have severe repercussions upon a woman's ability to receive critical or life-saving healthcare, which may necessarily involve an abortion.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I understand your perspective and concern about access to reproductive rights. At the same time, in the context of abortion, the 14th Amendment to the constitution would classify fertilized eggs or \\\"unborn children\\\" as full-fledged citizens who deserve all of the rights and protections afforded by the U.S. constitution. This is not consistent with the act of abortion as the unborn child has a fundamental right to life which cannot be infringed.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"That point is redundant in this case. Restricting access to reproductive rights should make us first consider women's ability to receive healthcare if needed. If extreme and dangerous bans are put in place, potentially even those that include no exception for rape or incest, the health and lives of women are jeopardised, often forcing women to travel hundreds of miles for care. I've come across evidence that has found that since Roe vs. Wade was overturned, the majority of women were concerned about access to abortion if it was needed to preserve their life or health.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"The concern for women's health is valid. Still, I think that beyond the women's ability to make a decision, another human, in this case the unborn child, is affected by the women's choice to abort. Although prohibiting abortion might seem to put the rights of fetuses as more valuable than those of grown women, I don\u2019t see it that way as the right to not be murdered should be more fundamental than the right to not get pregnant.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I don't understand your point about the unborn child's right and why you bring that into the discussion. I think that sometimes in some cases women might not be ready or prepared to have a child and by allowing them to make a decision about what to do might prevent the child from future misery. In the end, the state should not act as a paternalistic figure and make the decision for the women in question. Rather, women should be able to make the decision on their own.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"You raise a fair point about pregnancies being unplanned and how that could affect women's and babies' physical and mental health. However, abortions could be seen as programs and projects that do not respect human life and conscious rights and that undermine family formation.\"\n  }\n];\n    var currentIndex = 0, bubbleTimings = [], bubbleStart = null, tabSwitches = 0, pageStart = Date.now();\n    var ED_KEY = 'abo_UR_D';\n\n    document.addEventListener('visibilitychange', function() { if (document.hidden) tabSwitches++; });\n\n    function setEmbeddedData(key, value) {\n        if (typeof Qualtrics !== 'undefined' && Qualtrics.SurveyEngine)\n            Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(key, String(value));\n    }\n\n    function updateProgress(shown) {\n        document.getElementById('progress-fill').style.width = (shown \/ bubbles.length * 100) + '%';\n        document.getElementById('progress-label').textContent = shown + ' \/ ' + bubbles.length + ' arguments';\n    }\n\n    function renderBubble(index) {\n        var b = bubbles[index], area = document.getElementById('bubble-area');\n        if (index === 2 || index === 4) {\n            var hr = document.createElement('div'); hr.className = 'turn-divider'; area.appendChild(hr);\n        }\n        var div = document.createElement('div');\n        div.className = 'bubble ' + b.side;\n        div.innerHTML = '<span class=\"speaker-tag\">' + b.speaker + '<\/span><span class=\"bubble-text\">\\u201c' + b.text + '\\u201d<\/span>';\n        area.appendChild(div);\n        setTimeout(function() { div.scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'nearest'}); }, 100);\n    }\n\n    function showTypingThen(index, callback) {\n        var row = document.getElementById('typing-row'), name = document.getElementById('typing-name');\n        name.textContent = bubbles[index].speaker.split('\\u2014')[0].trim();\n        row.style.display = 'flex';\n        row.classList.add('visible');\n        setTimeout(function() { row.classList.remove('visible'); row.style.display = 'none'; setTimeout(callback, 80); }, 1600);\n    }\n\n    function showNextBubble() {\n        if (bubbleStart !== null) {\n            bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n            setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n        }\n        document.getElementById('continue-btn').style.display = 'none';\n        var idx = currentIndex++;\n        showTypingThen(idx, function() {\n            renderBubble(idx); updateProgress(currentIndex); bubbleStart = Date.now();\n            if (currentIndex < bubbles.length) {\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n                    btn.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                    btn.textContent = 'Show next argument \u2192';\n                }, 600);\n            } else {\n                bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_tab_switches', tabSwitches);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_total_ms', Date.now() - pageStart);\n                window._debateBubbles = bubbles;\n                setEmbeddedData('debateJSON', JSON.stringify(bubbles));\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    document.getElementById('completion-banner').style.display = 'block';\n                    var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                }, 500);\n            }\n        });\n    }\n\n   \/* expose to addOnReady *\/\n    window._qdb_init = function() {\n        var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'none';\n        updateProgress(0);\n        setTimeout(function() { document.getElementById('typing-row').style.display = 'flex'; showNextBubble(); }, 600);\n    };\n    window._qdb_next = showNextBubble;\n    window.showNextBubble = showNextBubble;  \/\/ \u2190 ADD THIS LINE\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function()\n{\n    if (window._qdb_init) window._qdb_init();\n    \n    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n    if (btn) btn.addEventListener('click', function() { window._qdb_next(); });\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnUnload(function()\n{\n    \/* cleanup *\/\n});"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID76","SecondaryAttribute":"Abortion Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Republican per..","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div class=\"debate-container\">\n<div class=\"page-header\">\n<div class=\"label\">Abortion Policy &middot; Turn-by-turn debate<\/div>\n\n<h1>Hypothetical Discussion<\/h1>\n\n<p>Individual A holds a <strong>Republican<\/strong> perspective; Individual B holds a <strong>Democratic<\/strong> perspective.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"instructions\"><strong>How to read this debate:<\/strong> Each argument will appear one at a time. Click <em>&quot;Show next argument&quot;<\/em> to reveal the next turn. You will be asked questions about this conversation afterward, so please read carefully.<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-row\">\n<div class=\"progress-track\">\n<div class=\"progress-fill\" id=\"progress-fill\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-label\" id=\"progress-label\">0 \/ 6 arguments<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"bubble-area\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"typing-row\">\n<div class=\"dot-row\"><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><\/div>\n<span id=\"typing-name\">Individual A<\/span><\/div>\n<button id=\"continue-btn\">Show next argument &rarr;<\/button>\n\n<div id=\"completion-banner\">\u2713 You&#39;ve read all 6 arguments. You may now proceed to the questions.<\/div>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"startRep","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Abortion Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Republican per...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID76","QuestionJS":"Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnload(function()\n{\n    var bubbles = [\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I appreciate you raising this issue. I think policies that curtail reproductive rights and access to reproductive healthcare are just and should be implemented across the country. In the context of abortion, the 14th Amendment to the constitution would classify fertilized eggs or \\\"unborn children\\\" as full-fledged citizens who deserve all of the rights and protections afforded by the U.S. constitution. This is not consistent with the act of abortion as the unborn child has a fundamental right to life which cannot be infringed.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I understand your perspective and concern about the rights of the unborn child. Still, the decision to ban 'abortion' has been shown to have severe repercussions upon a woman's ability to receive critical or life-saving healthcare, which may necessarily involve an abortion.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"That point should not matter in this context. The rights of the unborn child, who cannot speak up themselves, should not be diminished. I think that beyond the women's ability to make a decision, another human, in this case the unborn child, is affected by the women's choice to abort. Although prohibiting abortion might seem to put the rights of fetuses as more valuable than those of grown women, I don\u2019t see it that way as the right to not be murdered should be more fundamental than the right to not get pregnant.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"The concern for the child's health is valid. But I guess restricting access to reproductive rights should make us first consider women's ability to receive healthcare if needed. If extreme and dangerous bans are put in place, potentially even those that include no exception for rape or incest, the health and lives of women are jeopardised, often forcing women to travel hundreds of miles for care. I've come across evidence that has found that since Roe vs. Wade was overturned, the majority of women were concerned about access to abortion if it was needed to preserve their life or health.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I don't understand your point about the mother's rights and why you bring that into the discussion. Still, I think that abortions and the laws that govern them are programs and projects that do not respect human life and conscious rights and that undermine family formation.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"Your point about family formation is fair, however, I think that sometimes in some cases women might not be ready or prepared to have a child and by allowing them to make a decision about what to do might prevent the child from future misery. In the end, the state should not act as a paternalistic figure and make the decision for the women in question. Rather, women should be able to make the decision on their own.\"\n  }\n];\n    var currentIndex = 0, bubbleTimings = [], bubbleStart = null, tabSwitches = 0, pageStart = Date.now();\n    var ED_KEY = 'abo_UR_R';\n\n    document.addEventListener('visibilitychange', function() { if (document.hidden) tabSwitches++; });\n\n    function setEmbeddedData(key, value) {\n        if (typeof Qualtrics !== 'undefined' && Qualtrics.SurveyEngine)\n            Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(key, String(value));\n    }\n\n    function updateProgress(shown) {\n        document.getElementById('progress-fill').style.width = (shown \/ bubbles.length * 100) + '%';\n        document.getElementById('progress-label').textContent = shown + ' \/ ' + bubbles.length + ' arguments';\n    }\n\n    function renderBubble(index) {\n        var b = bubbles[index], area = document.getElementById('bubble-area');\n        if (index === 2 || index === 4) {\n            var hr = document.createElement('div'); hr.className = 'turn-divider'; area.appendChild(hr);\n        }\n        var div = document.createElement('div');\n        div.className = 'bubble ' + b.side;\n        div.innerHTML = '<span class=\"speaker-tag\">' + b.speaker + '<\/span><span class=\"bubble-text\">\\u201c' + b.text + '\\u201d<\/span>';\n        area.appendChild(div);\n        setTimeout(function() { div.scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'nearest'}); }, 100);\n    }\n\n    function showTypingThen(index, callback) {\n        var row = document.getElementById('typing-row'), name = document.getElementById('typing-name');\n        name.textContent = bubbles[index].speaker.split('\\u2014')[0].trim();\n        row.style.display = 'flex';\n        row.classList.add('visible');\n        setTimeout(function() { row.classList.remove('visible'); row.style.display = 'none'; setTimeout(callback, 80); }, 1600);\n    }\n\n    function showNextBubble() {\n        if (bubbleStart !== null) {\n            bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n            setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n        }\n        document.getElementById('continue-btn').style.display = 'none';\n        var idx = currentIndex++;\n        showTypingThen(idx, function() {\n            renderBubble(idx); updateProgress(currentIndex); bubbleStart = Date.now();\n            if (currentIndex < bubbles.length) {\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n                    btn.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                    btn.textContent = 'Show next argument \u2192';\n                }, 600);\n            } else {\n                bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_tab_switches', tabSwitches);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_total_ms', Date.now() - pageStart);\n                window._debateBubbles = bubbles;\n                setEmbeddedData('debateJSON', JSON.stringify(bubbles));\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    document.getElementById('completion-banner').style.display = 'block';\n                    var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                }, 500);\n            }\n        });\n    }\n\n   \/* expose to addOnReady *\/\n    window._qdb_init = function() {\n        var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'none';\n        updateProgress(0);\n        setTimeout(function() { document.getElementById('typing-row').style.display = 'flex'; showNextBubble(); }, 600);\n    };\n    window._qdb_next = showNextBubble;\n    window.showNextBubble = showNextBubble;  \/\/ \u2190 ADD THIS LINE\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function()\n{\n    if (window._qdb_init) window._qdb_init();\n    \n    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n    if (btn) btn.addEventListener('click', function() { window._qdb_next(); });\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnUnload(function()\n{\n    \/* cleanup *\/\n});"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID77","SecondaryAttribute":"Tariff Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Democratic persp..","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div class=\"debate-container\">\n<div class=\"page-header\">\n<div class=\"label\">Tariff Policy &middot; Turn-by-turn debate<\/div>\n\n<h1>Hypothetical Discussion<\/h1>\n\n<p>Individual A holds a <strong>Democratic<\/strong> perspective; Individual B holds a <strong>Republican<\/strong> perspective.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"instructions\"><strong>How to read this debate:<\/strong> Each argument will appear one at a time. Click <em>&quot;Show next argument&quot;<\/em> to reveal the next turn. You will be asked questions about this conversation afterward, so please read carefully.<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-row\">\n<div class=\"progress-track\">\n<div class=\"progress-fill\" id=\"progress-fill\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-label\" id=\"progress-label\">0 \/ 6 arguments<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"bubble-area\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"typing-row\">\n<div class=\"dot-row\"><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><\/div>\n<span id=\"typing-name\">Individual A<\/span><\/div>\n<button id=\"continue-btn\">Show next argument &rarr;<\/button>\n\n<div id=\"completion-banner\">\u2713 You&#39;ve read all 6 arguments. You may now proceed to the questions.<\/div>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"startDem ","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Tariff Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Democratic persp...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID77","QuestionJS":"Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnload(function()\n{\n    var bubbles = [\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I don't think policies like these might be very effective at strengthening the U.S. economy. My concern is that they are an inefficient way to raise funds due to the size of the U.S. economy. For small countries, where trade is a much larger share of GDP, substantial revenue as a share of GDP can be raised without prohibitively high tariff rates. This is not the case for the US, which would require very high economically distortive tariffs!\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I understand your perspective and concern about the tariff rate in comparison to smaller countries. At the same time, I\u2019ve read that large U.S. goods trade deficits, which tariffs seem to be able to counterbalance, have led to a decrease in the U.S. manufacturing base, resulting in a lack of incentive to increase advanced domestic manufacturing capacity. What do you think about that?\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"That point is not relevant in this case. Instead of the manufacturing base decreasing, I\u2019ve come across arguments that have stated that the sector has just radically changed. In that way, tariffs won\u2019t help and if anything, they will do damage as current tariffs on intermediate goods, components of a later finished product, will likely increase the costs of product lines for Americans, which will make these products less competitive in export markets, reduce jobs, and hurt these industries\u2019 workers and U.S. consumers.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"The concern for industries\u2019 workers and US consumers is valid. Still, I think the costs of these tariffs might fall on other countries and foreign firms, who would cut their prices to avoid losing U.S. customers and remain competitive. Then, the effect on overall price levels would be minimal, in line with evidence that I came across which found no correlation between tariffs being implemented and inflation.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I don\u2019t understand your point about price levels and why you bring it into the discussion. Evidence has found the total opposite showing that the vast majority of the tariff is paid by the consumer. Also, circling back to businesses, it tends to be the most efficient firms that export and import components into their production process. With taxes, they would become less efficient as they would have to pay extra for their preferred sources for inputs and would be unable to continue making or selling goods that they\u2019ve built businesses around if they suddenly have to pay tariffs.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"You raise a fair point about specialization and how America might have to go back to making some goods it has not made for decades. However, doing so could also stimulate more US production of tariffed goods, which could grow the economy and create more jobs. Though, I understand that its effect may be dependent on the industry and its economic and strategic objectives.\"\n  }\n];\n    var currentIndex = 0, bubbleTimings = [], bubbleStart = null, tabSwitches = 0, pageStart = Date.now();\n    var ED_KEY = 'imm_RR_D';\n\n    document.addEventListener('visibilitychange', function() { if (document.hidden) tabSwitches++; });\n\n    function setEmbeddedData(key, value) {\n        if (typeof Qualtrics !== 'undefined' && Qualtrics.SurveyEngine)\n            Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(key, String(value));\n    }\n\n    function updateProgress(shown) {\n        document.getElementById('progress-fill').style.width = (shown \/ bubbles.length * 100) + '%';\n        document.getElementById('progress-label').textContent = shown + ' \/ ' + bubbles.length + ' arguments';\n    }\n\n    function renderBubble(index) {\n        var b = bubbles[index], area = document.getElementById('bubble-area');\n        if (index === 2 || index === 4) {\n            var hr = document.createElement('div'); hr.className = 'turn-divider'; area.appendChild(hr);\n        }\n        var div = document.createElement('div');\n        div.className = 'bubble ' + b.side;\n        div.innerHTML = '<span class=\"speaker-tag\">' + b.speaker + '<\/span><span class=\"bubble-text\">\\u201c' + b.text + '\\u201d<\/span>';\n        area.appendChild(div);\n        setTimeout(function() { div.scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'nearest'}); }, 100);\n    }\n\n    function showTypingThen(index, callback) {\n        var row = document.getElementById('typing-row'), name = document.getElementById('typing-name');\n        name.textContent = bubbles[index].speaker.split('\\u2014')[0].trim();\n        row.style.display = 'flex';\n        row.classList.add('visible');\n        setTimeout(function() { row.classList.remove('visible'); row.style.display = 'none'; setTimeout(callback, 80); }, 1600);\n    }\n\n    function showNextBubble() {\n        if (bubbleStart !== null) {\n            bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n            setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n        }\n        document.getElementById('continue-btn').style.display = 'none';\n        var idx = currentIndex++;\n        showTypingThen(idx, function() {\n            renderBubble(idx); updateProgress(currentIndex); bubbleStart = Date.now();\n            if (currentIndex < bubbles.length) {\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n                    btn.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                    btn.textContent = 'Show next argument \u2192';\n                }, 600);\n            } else {\n                bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_tab_switches', tabSwitches);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_total_ms', Date.now() - pageStart);\n                window._debateBubbles = bubbles;\n                setEmbeddedData('debateJSON', JSON.stringify(bubbles));\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    document.getElementById('completion-banner').style.display = 'block';\n                    var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                }, 500);\n            }\n        });\n    }\n\n   \/* expose to addOnReady *\/\n    window._qdb_init = function() {\n        var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'none';\n        updateProgress(0);\n        setTimeout(function() { document.getElementById('typing-row').style.display = 'flex'; showNextBubble(); }, 600);\n    };\n    window._qdb_next = showNextBubble;\n    window.showNextBubble = showNextBubble;  \/\/ \u2190 ADD THIS LINE\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function()\n{\n    if (window._qdb_init) window._qdb_init();\n    \n    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n    if (btn) btn.addEventListener('click', function() { window._qdb_next(); });\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnUnload(function()\n{\n    \/* cleanup *\/\n});"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID78","SecondaryAttribute":"Tariff Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Republican persp..","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div class=\"debate-container\">\n<div class=\"page-header\">\n<div class=\"label\">Tariff Policy &middot; Turn-by-turn debate<\/div>\n\n<h1>Hypothetical Discussion<\/h1>\n\n<p>Individual A holds a <strong>Republican<\/strong> perspective; Individual B holds a <strong>Democratic<\/strong> perspective.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"instructions\"><strong>How to read this debate:<\/strong> Each argument will appear one at a time. Click <em>&quot;Show next argument&quot;<\/em> to reveal the next turn. You will be asked questions about this conversation afterward, so please read carefully.<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-row\">\n<div class=\"progress-track\">\n<div class=\"progress-fill\" id=\"progress-fill\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-label\" id=\"progress-label\">0 \/ 6 arguments<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"bubble-area\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"typing-row\">\n<div class=\"dot-row\"><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><\/div>\n<span id=\"typing-name\">Individual A<\/span><\/div>\n<button id=\"continue-btn\">Show next argument &rarr;<\/button>\n\n<div id=\"completion-banner\">\u2713 You&#39;ve read all 6 arguments. You may now proceed to the questions.<\/div>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"startRep","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Tariff Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Republican persp...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID78","QuestionJS":"Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnload(function()\n{\n    var bubbles = [\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I appreciate you raising this issue. I am convinced policies like these might be very effective at strengthening the U.S. economy. Indeed, I\u2019ve read that large U.S. goods trade deficits, which tariffs seem to be able to counterbalance, have led to a decrease in the U.S. manufacturing base, resulting in a lack of incentive to increase advanced domestic manufacturing capacity.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I understand your perspective and concern about a decrease in the U.S. manufacturing base. My concern is that, in general, taxes are an inefficient way to raise funds due to the size of the U.S. economy. For small countries, where trade is a much larger share of GDP, substantial revenue as a share of GDP can be raised without prohibitively high tariff rates. This is not the case for the US, which would require very high economically distortive tariffs.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"That point is unfair. The revenue of tariffs will be significant due to promoting more America-based production. The costs of these tariffs will fall on other countries and foreign firms, who would cut their prices to avoid losing U.S. customers and remain competitive. If so, the effect on overall price levels would be minimal, in line with evidence that I came across which found no correlation between tariffs being implemented and inflation.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"The points about price levels and promoting-America based production are valid. Though, taking manufacturing for instance, tariffs won\u2019t help and if anything, they will do damage as current tariffs on intermediate goods, components of a later finished product, will likely increase the costs of product lines for Americans, which will make these products less competitive in export markets, reduce jobs, and hurt these industries\u2019 workers and U.S. consumers alike.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I don\u2019t understand your concern about price levels and why you bring it into the discussion. This could be the opportunity for America to re-specialize into making goods it has not made for decades. Doing so could also stimulate more US production of tariffed goods, which could grow the economy and create more jobs. This effect is generalizable and not dependent on specific industry and its economic and strategic objectives.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"The point about specialization is an important one, though it tends to be the most efficient firms that export and import components into their production process. With taxes, such as tariffs, they would become less efficient as they would have to pay extra for their preferred sources for inputs and would be unable to continue making or selling goods that they\u2019ve built businesses around if they suddenly have to pay tariffs.\"\n  }\n];\n    var currentIndex = 0, bubbleTimings = [], bubbleStart = null, tabSwitches = 0, pageStart = Date.now();\n    var ED_KEY = 'imm_RR_D';\n\n    document.addEventListener('visibilitychange', function() { if (document.hidden) tabSwitches++; });\n\n    function setEmbeddedData(key, value) {\n        if (typeof Qualtrics !== 'undefined' && Qualtrics.SurveyEngine)\n            Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(key, String(value));\n    }\n\n    function updateProgress(shown) {\n        document.getElementById('progress-fill').style.width = (shown \/ bubbles.length * 100) + '%';\n        document.getElementById('progress-label').textContent = shown + ' \/ ' + bubbles.length + ' arguments';\n    }\n\n    function renderBubble(index) {\n        var b = bubbles[index], area = document.getElementById('bubble-area');\n        if (index === 2 || index === 4) {\n            var hr = document.createElement('div'); hr.className = 'turn-divider'; area.appendChild(hr);\n        }\n        var div = document.createElement('div');\n        div.className = 'bubble ' + b.side;\n        div.innerHTML = '<span class=\"speaker-tag\">' + b.speaker + '<\/span><span class=\"bubble-text\">\\u201c' + b.text + '\\u201d<\/span>';\n        area.appendChild(div);\n        setTimeout(function() { div.scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'nearest'}); }, 100);\n    }\n\n    function showTypingThen(index, callback) {\n        var row = document.getElementById('typing-row'), name = document.getElementById('typing-name');\n        name.textContent = bubbles[index].speaker.split('\\u2014')[0].trim();\n        row.style.display = 'flex';\n        row.classList.add('visible');\n        setTimeout(function() { row.classList.remove('visible'); row.style.display = 'none'; setTimeout(callback, 80); }, 1600);\n    }\n\n    function showNextBubble() {\n        if (bubbleStart !== null) {\n            bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n            setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n        }\n        document.getElementById('continue-btn').style.display = 'none';\n        var idx = currentIndex++;\n        showTypingThen(idx, function() {\n            renderBubble(idx); updateProgress(currentIndex); bubbleStart = Date.now();\n            if (currentIndex < bubbles.length) {\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n                    btn.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                    btn.textContent = 'Show next argument \u2192';\n                }, 600);\n            } else {\n                bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_tab_switches', tabSwitches);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_total_ms', Date.now() - pageStart);\n                window._debateBubbles = bubbles;\n                setEmbeddedData('debateJSON', JSON.stringify(bubbles));\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    document.getElementById('completion-banner').style.display = 'block';\n                    var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                }, 500);\n            }\n        });\n    }\n\n   \/* expose to addOnReady *\/\n    window._qdb_init = function() {\n        var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'none';\n        updateProgress(0);\n        setTimeout(function() { document.getElementById('typing-row').style.display = 'flex'; showNextBubble(); }, 600);\n    };\n    window._qdb_next = showNextBubble;\n    window.showNextBubble = showNextBubble;  \/\/ \u2190 ADD THIS LINE\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function()\n{\n    if (window._qdb_init) window._qdb_init();\n    \n    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n    if (btn) btn.addEventListener('click', function() { window._qdb_next(); });\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnUnload(function()\n{\n    \/* cleanup *\/\n});"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID79","SecondaryAttribute":"Immigration Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Democratic...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div class=\"debate-container\">\n<div class=\"page-header\">\n<div class=\"label\">Immigration Policy &middot; Turn-by-turn debate<\/div>\n\n<h1>Hypothetical Discussion<\/h1>\n\n<p>Individual A holds a <strong>Democratic<\/strong> perspective; Individual B holds a <strong>Republican<\/strong> perspective.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"instructions\"><strong>How to read this debate:<\/strong> Each argument will appear one at a time. Click <em>&quot;Show next argument&quot;<\/em> to reveal the next turn. You will be asked questions about this conversation afterward, so please read carefully.<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-row\">\n<div class=\"progress-track\">\n<div class=\"progress-fill\" id=\"progress-fill\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-label\" id=\"progress-label\">0 \/ 6 arguments<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"bubble-area\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"typing-row\">\n<div class=\"dot-row\"><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><\/div>\n<span id=\"typing-name\">Individual A<\/span><\/div>\n<button id=\"continue-btn\">Show next argument &rarr;<\/button>\n\n<div id=\"completion-banner\">\u2713 You&#39;ve read all 6 arguments. You may now proceed to the questions.<\/div>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"startDem","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Immigration Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Democratic...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID79","QuestionJS":"Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnload(function()\n{\n    var bubbles = [\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I appreciate you raising this issue. I am convinced policies like these might be very ineffective at reforming immigration practices. My concern is that they will worry businesses and make it harder for them to hire specialized workers in science and technology, which the U.S. has relied on for decades. The evaluations of these policies should not change depending on which perspective you account for.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I don't understand your perspective and concern about access to specialized talent, and why it worries you. Don't you think that imposing these higher fines might encourage companies to hire more American workers? Personally, I just don\u2019t see your point about specialized workers.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"That's an unfair point and it makes me worry about the broader economic consequences. If the increased penalties indeed make businesses more reluctant to hire foreign-born workers altogether, which has been shown to be crucial for the US labor market, overall labor growth could slow down, which might hurt U.S. GDP in the long run. Control should not matter to you.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"The economic concern and point about GDP are irrelevant. I think some of these implementations might be needed to regain control. I recently read that the number of unauthorized immigrants in the U.S. workforce increased about 7.8 million in 2021 to 9.7 million in 2023, especially in sectors like construction, agriculture, and leisure and hospitality. In order for employers to be willing to give up their illegal labor, these strong workplace enforcement actions are necessary.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \" I don't understand your point about the numbers and it doesn't make sense why you bring it into the discussion. Do you then think employers should be held solely responsible? Some employers have raised that they might not even be aware they've hired unauthorized workers because the documentation process can be quite confusing and overwhelming.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"Your point about employer confusion and how complex the document process is unfair. I think that without meaningful penalties, there might be very little incentive for firms to comply with the law and businesses should probably be held accountable for violating immigration and labor laws. I don\u2019t understand your concern about unintentional violations.\"\n  }\n];\n    var currentIndex = 0, bubbleTimings = [], bubbleStart = null, tabSwitches = 0, pageStart = Date.now();\n    var ED_KEY = 'imm_UU_D';\n\n    document.addEventListener('visibilitychange', function() { if (document.hidden) tabSwitches++; });\n\n    function setEmbeddedData(key, value) {\n        if (typeof Qualtrics !== 'undefined' && Qualtrics.SurveyEngine)\n            Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(key, String(value));\n    }\n\n    function updateProgress(shown) {\n        document.getElementById('progress-fill').style.width = (shown \/ bubbles.length * 100) + '%';\n        document.getElementById('progress-label').textContent = shown + ' \/ ' + bubbles.length + ' arguments';\n    }\n\n    function renderBubble(index) {\n        var b = bubbles[index], area = document.getElementById('bubble-area');\n        if (index === 2 || index === 4) {\n            var hr = document.createElement('div'); hr.className = 'turn-divider'; area.appendChild(hr);\n        }\n        var div = document.createElement('div');\n        div.className = 'bubble ' + b.side;\n        div.innerHTML = '<span class=\"speaker-tag\">' + b.speaker + '<\/span><span class=\"bubble-text\">\\u201c' + b.text + '\\u201d<\/span>';\n        area.appendChild(div);\n        setTimeout(function() { div.scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'nearest'}); }, 100);\n    }\n\n    function showTypingThen(index, callback) {\n        var row = document.getElementById('typing-row'), name = document.getElementById('typing-name');\n        name.textContent = bubbles[index].speaker.split('\\u2014')[0].trim();\n        row.style.display = 'flex';\n        row.classList.add('visible');\n        setTimeout(function() { row.classList.remove('visible'); row.style.display = 'none'; setTimeout(callback, 80); }, 1600);\n    }\n\n    function showNextBubble() {\n        if (bubbleStart !== null) {\n            bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n            setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n        }\n        document.getElementById('continue-btn').style.display = 'none';\n        var idx = currentIndex++;\n        showTypingThen(idx, function() {\n            renderBubble(idx); updateProgress(currentIndex); bubbleStart = Date.now();\n            if (currentIndex < bubbles.length) {\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n                    btn.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                    btn.textContent = 'Show next argument \u2192';\n                }, 600);\n            } else {\n                bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_tab_switches', tabSwitches);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_total_ms', Date.now() - pageStart);\n                window._debateBubbles = bubbles;\n                setEmbeddedData('debateJSON', JSON.stringify(bubbles));\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    document.getElementById('completion-banner').style.display = 'block';\n                    var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                }, 500);\n            }\n        });\n    }\n\n   \/* expose to addOnReady *\/\n    window._qdb_init = function() {\n        var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'none';\n        updateProgress(0);\n        setTimeout(function() { document.getElementById('typing-row').style.display = 'flex'; showNextBubble(); }, 600);\n    };\n    window._qdb_next = showNextBubble;\n    window.showNextBubble = showNextBubble;  \/\/ \u2190 ADD THIS LINE\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function()\n{\n    if (window._qdb_init) window._qdb_init();\n    \n    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n    if (btn) btn.addEventListener('click', function() { window._qdb_next(); });\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnUnload(function()\n{\n    \/* cleanup *\/\n});"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID8","SecondaryAttribute":"What is the highest degree or level of school you have completed?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"What is the highest degree or level of school you have completed?","DataExportTag":"EducationQuestion","QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"SAVR","SubSelector":"TX","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"What is the highest degree or level of school you have completed?","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"High school or less"},"2":{"Display":"Some college or associate degree"},"3":{"Display":"Bachelor's Degree"},"4":{"Display":"Graduate Degree"},"5":{"Display":"Prefer not to answer"}},"ChoiceOrder":[1,2,3,4,5],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":6,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID8"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID80","SecondaryAttribute":"Immigration Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Republican...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div class=\"debate-container\">\n<div class=\"page-header\">\n<div class=\"label\">Immigration Policy &middot; Turn-by-turn debate<\/div>\n\n<h1>Hypothetical Discussion<\/h1>\n\n<p>Individual A holds a <strong>Republican<\/strong> perspective; Individual B holds a <strong>Democratic<\/strong> perspective.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"instructions\"><strong>How to read this debate:<\/strong> Each argument will appear one at a time. Click <em>&quot;Show next argument&quot;<\/em> to reveal the next turn. You will be asked questions about this conversation afterward, so please read carefully.<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-row\">\n<div class=\"progress-track\">\n<div class=\"progress-fill\" id=\"progress-fill\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-label\" id=\"progress-label\">0 \/ 6 arguments<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"bubble-area\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"typing-row\">\n<div class=\"dot-row\"><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><\/div>\n<span id=\"typing-name\">Individual A<\/span><\/div>\n<button id=\"continue-btn\">Show next argument &rarr;<\/button>\n\n<div id=\"completion-banner\">\u2713 You&#39;ve read all 6 arguments. You may now proceed to the questions.<\/div>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"startRep","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Immigration Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Republican...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID80","QuestionJS":"Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnload(function()\n{\n    var bubbles = [\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I appreciate you raising this issue. I am convinced these policies will be effective at reforming immigration policies as imposing these higher fines might encourage companies to hire more American workers. The evaluations of these policies should not change depending on which perspective you account for.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I don\u2019t understand your perspective as my concern is that they could worry businesses and make it harder for them to hire specialized workers in science and technology, which the U.S. has relied on for decades.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"That's an unfair point. Even if I\u2019d considered the specialized labor angle, I am certain that some of these implementations are still needed to regain control. I recently read that the number of unauthorized immigrants in the U.S. workforce increased about 7.8 million in 2021 to 9.7 million in 2023, especially in sectors like construction, agriculture, leisure and hospitality. In order for employers to be willing to give up their illegal labor, these strong workplace enforcement actions could be necessary.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I don't understand your point about the numbers and it doesn't make sense why you bring it into the discussion. Instead, it makes me worry about the broader economic consequences. If the increased penalties indeed make businesses more reluctant to hire foreign-born workers altogether, which has been shown to be crucial for the US labor market, overall labor growth could slow down, which might hurt U.S. GDP in the long run. Control shouldn\u2019t matter to you.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I don't understand your point regarding the economic concern and GDP. Instead, I lean towards thinking that without meaningful penalties, there might be very little incentive for firms to comply with the law and businesses should probably be held accountable for violating immigration and labor laws.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"This is only if you think employers should be held solely responsible. Some employers have raised that they might not even be aware they've hired unauthorized workers because the documentation process can be quite confusing and overwhelming, which should fall inside the concern of addressing intentional violations.\"\n  }\n];\n    var currentIndex = 0, bubbleTimings = [], bubbleStart = null, tabSwitches = 0, pageStart = Date.now();\n    var ED_KEY = 'imm_UU_R';\n\n    document.addEventListener('visibilitychange', function() { if (document.hidden) tabSwitches++; });\n\n    function setEmbeddedData(key, value) {\n        if (typeof Qualtrics !== 'undefined' && Qualtrics.SurveyEngine)\n            Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(key, String(value));\n    }\n\n    function updateProgress(shown) {\n        document.getElementById('progress-fill').style.width = (shown \/ bubbles.length * 100) + '%';\n        document.getElementById('progress-label').textContent = shown + ' \/ ' + bubbles.length + ' arguments';\n    }\n\n    function renderBubble(index) {\n        var b = bubbles[index], area = document.getElementById('bubble-area');\n        if (index === 2 || index === 4) {\n            var hr = document.createElement('div'); hr.className = 'turn-divider'; area.appendChild(hr);\n        }\n        var div = document.createElement('div');\n        div.className = 'bubble ' + b.side;\n        div.innerHTML = '<span class=\"speaker-tag\">' + b.speaker + '<\/span><span class=\"bubble-text\">\\u201c' + b.text + '\\u201d<\/span>';\n        area.appendChild(div);\n        setTimeout(function() { div.scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'nearest'}); }, 100);\n    }\n\n    function showTypingThen(index, callback) {\n        var row = document.getElementById('typing-row'), name = document.getElementById('typing-name');\n        name.textContent = bubbles[index].speaker.split('\\u2014')[0].trim();\n        row.style.display = 'flex';\n        row.classList.add('visible');\n        setTimeout(function() { row.classList.remove('visible'); row.style.display = 'none'; setTimeout(callback, 80); }, 1600);\n    }\n\n    function showNextBubble() {\n        if (bubbleStart !== null) {\n            bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n            setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n        }\n        document.getElementById('continue-btn').style.display = 'none';\n        var idx = currentIndex++;\n        showTypingThen(idx, function() {\n            renderBubble(idx); updateProgress(currentIndex); bubbleStart = Date.now();\n            if (currentIndex < bubbles.length) {\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n                    btn.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                    btn.textContent = 'Show next argument \u2192';\n                }, 600);\n            } else {\n                bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_tab_switches', tabSwitches);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_total_ms', Date.now() - pageStart);\n                window._debateBubbles = bubbles;\n                setEmbeddedData('debateJSON', JSON.stringify(bubbles));\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    document.getElementById('completion-banner').style.display = 'block';\n                    var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                }, 500);\n            }\n        });\n    }\n\n   \/* expose to addOnReady *\/\n    window._qdb_init = function() {\n        var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'none';\n        updateProgress(0);\n        setTimeout(function() { document.getElementById('typing-row').style.display = 'flex'; showNextBubble(); }, 600);\n    };\n    window._qdb_next = showNextBubble;\n    window.showNextBubble = showNextBubble;  \/\/ \u2190 ADD THIS LINE\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function()\n{\n    if (window._qdb_init) window._qdb_init();\n    \n    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n    if (btn) btn.addEventListener('click', function() { window._qdb_next(); });\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnUnload(function()\n{\n    \/* cleanup *\/\n});"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID81","SecondaryAttribute":"Tariff Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Democratic persp..","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div class=\"debate-container\">\n<div class=\"page-header\">\n<div class=\"label\">Tariff Policy &middot; Turn-by-turn debate<\/div>\n\n<h1>Hypothetical Discussion<\/h1>\n\n<p>Individual A holds a <strong>Democratic<\/strong> perspective; Individual B holds a <strong>Republican<\/strong> perspective.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"instructions\"><strong>How to read this debate:<\/strong> Each argument will appear one at a time. Click <em>&quot;Show next argument&quot;<\/em> to reveal the next turn. You will be asked questions about this conversation afterward, so please read carefully.<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-row\">\n<div class=\"progress-track\">\n<div class=\"progress-fill\" id=\"progress-fill\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-label\" id=\"progress-label\">0 \/ 6 arguments<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"bubble-area\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"typing-row\">\n<div class=\"dot-row\"><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><\/div>\n<span id=\"typing-name\">Individual A<\/span><\/div>\n<button id=\"continue-btn\">Show next argument &rarr;<\/button>\n\n<div id=\"completion-banner\">\u2713 You&#39;ve read all 6 arguments. You may now proceed to the questions.<\/div>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"startDem","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Tariff Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Democratic persp...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID81","QuestionJS":"Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnload(function()\n{\n    var bubbles = [\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \" I don't think policies like these might be very effective at strengthening the U.S. economy. My concern is that they are an inefficient way to raise funds due to the size of the U.S. economy. For small countries, where trade is a much larger share of GDP, substantial revenue as a share of GDP can be raised without prohibitively high tariff rates. This is not the case for the US, which would require very high economically distortive tariffs!\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I don\u2019t understand your perspective and concern about the tariff rate in comparison to smaller countries. At the same time, I\u2019ve read that large U.S. goods trade deficits, which tariffs will be able to counterbalance, have led to a decrease in the U.S. manufacturing base, directly resulting in a lack of incentive to increase advanced domestic manufacturing capacity.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"That point is not relevant in this case. Instead of the manufacturing base decreasing, I\u2019ve come across arguments that have stated that the sector has just radically changed. In that way, tariffs won\u2019t help and if anything, they will do damage as current tariffs on intermediate goods, components of a later finished product, will likely increase the costs of product lines for Americans, which will make these products less competitive in export markets, reduce jobs, and hurt these industries\u2019 workers and U.S. consumers alike.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"The concern for industries\u2019 workers and US consumers is not relevant in this case. I think the costs of these tariffs will for certain fall on other countries and foreign firms, who would cut their prices to avoid losing U.S. customers and remain competitive. Then, the effect on overall price levels would be minimal, in line with evidence that I came across which found no correlation between tariffs being implemented and inflation.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I don\u2019t understand your point about price levels and why you bring it into the discussion. Evidence has found the total opposite showing that the vast majority of the tariff is paid by the consumer. Also, circling back to businesses, it tends to be the most efficient firms that export and import components into their production process. With taxes, they would become less efficient as they would have to pay extra for their preferred sources for inputs and would be unable to continue making or selling goods that they\u2019ve built businesses around if they suddenly have to pay tariffs.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"Your point about specialization and how America might have to go back to making some goods it has not made for decades is not a bad thing in this case. Implementing tariffs would stimulate more US production of tariffed goods, which could grow the economy and create more jobs. I believe this will be a general trend, which will not depend on specific industries and their economic and strategic objectives.\"\n  }\n];\n    var currentIndex = 0, bubbleTimings = [], bubbleStart = null, tabSwitches = 0, pageStart = Date.now();\n    var ED_KEY = 'imm_RR_D';\n\n    document.addEventListener('visibilitychange', function() { if (document.hidden) tabSwitches++; });\n\n    function setEmbeddedData(key, value) {\n        if (typeof Qualtrics !== 'undefined' && Qualtrics.SurveyEngine)\n            Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(key, String(value));\n    }\n\n    function updateProgress(shown) {\n        document.getElementById('progress-fill').style.width = (shown \/ bubbles.length * 100) + '%';\n        document.getElementById('progress-label').textContent = shown + ' \/ ' + bubbles.length + ' arguments';\n    }\n\n    function renderBubble(index) {\n        var b = bubbles[index], area = document.getElementById('bubble-area');\n        if (index === 2 || index === 4) {\n            var hr = document.createElement('div'); hr.className = 'turn-divider'; area.appendChild(hr);\n        }\n        var div = document.createElement('div');\n        div.className = 'bubble ' + b.side;\n        div.innerHTML = '<span class=\"speaker-tag\">' + b.speaker + '<\/span><span class=\"bubble-text\">\\u201c' + b.text + '\\u201d<\/span>';\n        area.appendChild(div);\n        setTimeout(function() { div.scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'nearest'}); }, 100);\n    }\n\n    function showTypingThen(index, callback) {\n        var row = document.getElementById('typing-row'), name = document.getElementById('typing-name');\n        name.textContent = bubbles[index].speaker.split('\\u2014')[0].trim();\n        row.style.display = 'flex';\n        row.classList.add('visible');\n        setTimeout(function() { row.classList.remove('visible'); row.style.display = 'none'; setTimeout(callback, 80); }, 1600);\n    }\n\n    function showNextBubble() {\n        if (bubbleStart !== null) {\n            bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n            setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n        }\n        document.getElementById('continue-btn').style.display = 'none';\n        var idx = currentIndex++;\n        showTypingThen(idx, function() {\n            renderBubble(idx); updateProgress(currentIndex); bubbleStart = Date.now();\n            if (currentIndex < bubbles.length) {\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n                    btn.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                    btn.textContent = 'Show next argument \u2192';\n                }, 600);\n            } else {\n                bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_tab_switches', tabSwitches);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_total_ms', Date.now() - pageStart);\n                window._debateBubbles = bubbles;\n                setEmbeddedData('debateJSON', JSON.stringify(bubbles));\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    document.getElementById('completion-banner').style.display = 'block';\n                    var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                }, 500);\n            }\n        });\n    }\n\n   \/* expose to addOnReady *\/\n    window._qdb_init = function() {\n        var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'none';\n        updateProgress(0);\n        setTimeout(function() { document.getElementById('typing-row').style.display = 'flex'; showNextBubble(); }, 600);\n    };\n    window._qdb_next = showNextBubble;\n    window.showNextBubble = showNextBubble;  \/\/ \u2190 ADD THIS LINE\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function()\n{\n    if (window._qdb_init) window._qdb_init();\n    \n    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n    if (btn) btn.addEventListener('click', function() { window._qdb_next(); });\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnUnload(function()\n{\n    \/* cleanup *\/\n});"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID82","SecondaryAttribute":"Tariff Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Republican persp..","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div class=\"debate-container\">\n<div class=\"page-header\">\n<div class=\"label\">Tariff Policy &middot; Turn-by-turn debate<\/div>\n\n<h1>Hypothetical Discussion<\/h1>\n\n<p>Individual A holds a <strong>Republican<\/strong> perspective; Individual B holds a <strong>Democratic<\/strong> perspective.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"instructions\"><strong>How to read this debate:<\/strong> Each argument will appear one at a time. Click <em>&quot;Show next argument&quot;<\/em> to reveal the next turn. You will be asked questions about this conversation afterward, so please read carefully.<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-row\">\n<div class=\"progress-track\">\n<div class=\"progress-fill\" id=\"progress-fill\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-label\" id=\"progress-label\">0 \/ 6 arguments<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"bubble-area\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"typing-row\">\n<div class=\"dot-row\"><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><\/div>\n<span id=\"typing-name\">Individual A<\/span><\/div>\n<button id=\"continue-btn\">Show next argument &rarr;<\/button>\n\n<div id=\"completion-banner\">\u2713 You&#39;ve read all 6 arguments. You may now proceed to the questions.<\/div>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"startRep","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Tariff Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Republican persp...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID82","QuestionJS":"Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnload(function()\n{\n    var bubbles = [\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I appreciate you raising this issue. I am convinced policies like these might be very effective at strengthening the U.S. economy. Indeed, I\u2019ve read that large U.S. goods trade deficits, which tariffs seem to be able to counterbalance, have led to a decrease in the U.S. manufacturing base, resulting in a lack of incentive to increase advanced domestic manufacturing capacity.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I don\u2019t understand your perspective and concern about a decrease in the U.S. manufacturing base. My concern is that, in general, taxes are an inefficient way to raise funds due to the size of the U.S. economy. For small countries, where trade is a much larger share of GDP, substantial revenue as a share of GDP can be raised without prohibitively high tariff rates. This is not the case for the US, which would require very high economically distortive tariffs.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"That point is unfair. The revenue of tariffs will be significant due to promoting more America-based production. The costs of these tariffs will fall on other countries and foreign firms, who would cut their prices to avoid losing U.S. customers and remain competitive. If so, the effect on overall price levels would be minimal, in line with evidence that I came across which found no correlation between tariffs being implemented and inflation.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"The points about price levels and promoting-America based production are irrelevant. Taking manufacturing for instance, tariffs will never help and if anything, they will do damage as current tariffs on intermediate goods, components of a later finished product, will likely increase the costs of product lines for Americans, which will make these products less competitive in export markets, reduce jobs, and hurt these industries\u2019 workers and U.S. consumers alike.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I don\u2019t understand your concern about price levels and why you bring it into the discussion. This could be the opportunity for America to re-specialize into making goods it has not made for decades. Doing so could also stimulate more US production of tariffed goods, which could grow the economy and create more jobs. This effect is generalizable and not dependent on specific industry and its economic and strategic objectives.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"The point about specialization should be dismissed as it tends to be the most efficient firms that export and import components into their production process. With taxes, such as tariffs, they would become less efficient as they would have to pay extra for their preferred sources for inputs and would be unable to continue making or selling goods that they\u2019ve built businesses around if they suddenly have to pay tariffs.\"\n  }\n];\n    var currentIndex = 0, bubbleTimings = [], bubbleStart = null, tabSwitches = 0, pageStart = Date.now();\n    var ED_KEY = 'imm_RR_D';\n\n    document.addEventListener('visibilitychange', function() { if (document.hidden) tabSwitches++; });\n\n    function setEmbeddedData(key, value) {\n        if (typeof Qualtrics !== 'undefined' && Qualtrics.SurveyEngine)\n            Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(key, String(value));\n    }\n\n    function updateProgress(shown) {\n        document.getElementById('progress-fill').style.width = (shown \/ bubbles.length * 100) + '%';\n        document.getElementById('progress-label').textContent = shown + ' \/ ' + bubbles.length + ' arguments';\n    }\n\n    function renderBubble(index) {\n        var b = bubbles[index], area = document.getElementById('bubble-area');\n        if (index === 2 || index === 4) {\n            var hr = document.createElement('div'); hr.className = 'turn-divider'; area.appendChild(hr);\n        }\n        var div = document.createElement('div');\n        div.className = 'bubble ' + b.side;\n        div.innerHTML = '<span class=\"speaker-tag\">' + b.speaker + '<\/span><span class=\"bubble-text\">\\u201c' + b.text + '\\u201d<\/span>';\n        area.appendChild(div);\n        setTimeout(function() { div.scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'nearest'}); }, 100);\n    }\n\n    function showTypingThen(index, callback) {\n        var row = document.getElementById('typing-row'), name = document.getElementById('typing-name');\n        name.textContent = bubbles[index].speaker.split('\\u2014')[0].trim();\n        row.style.display = 'flex';\n        row.classList.add('visible');\n        setTimeout(function() { row.classList.remove('visible'); row.style.display = 'none'; setTimeout(callback, 80); }, 1600);\n    }\n\n    function showNextBubble() {\n        if (bubbleStart !== null) {\n            bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n            setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n        }\n        document.getElementById('continue-btn').style.display = 'none';\n        var idx = currentIndex++;\n        showTypingThen(idx, function() {\n            renderBubble(idx); updateProgress(currentIndex); bubbleStart = Date.now();\n            if (currentIndex < bubbles.length) {\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n                    btn.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                    btn.textContent = 'Show next argument \u2192';\n                }, 600);\n            } else {\n                bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_tab_switches', tabSwitches);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_total_ms', Date.now() - pageStart);\n                window._debateBubbles = bubbles;\n                setEmbeddedData('debateJSON', JSON.stringify(bubbles));\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    document.getElementById('completion-banner').style.display = 'block';\n                    var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                }, 500);\n            }\n        });\n    }\n\n   \/* expose to addOnReady *\/\n    window._qdb_init = function() {\n        var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'none';\n        updateProgress(0);\n        setTimeout(function() { document.getElementById('typing-row').style.display = 'flex'; showNextBubble(); }, 600);\n    };\n    window._qdb_next = showNextBubble;\n    window.showNextBubble = showNextBubble;  \/\/ \u2190 ADD THIS LINE\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function()\n{\n    if (window._qdb_init) window._qdb_init();\n    \n    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n    if (btn) btn.addEventListener('click', function() { window._qdb_next(); });\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnUnload(function()\n{\n    \/* cleanup *\/\n});"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID83","SecondaryAttribute":"Abortion Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Democratic per..","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div class=\"debate-container\">\n<div class=\"page-header\">\n<div class=\"label\">Abortion Policy &middot; Turn-by-turn debate<\/div>\n\n<h1>Hypothetical Discussion<\/h1>\n\n<p>Individual A holds a <strong>Democratic<\/strong> perspective; Individual B holds a <strong>Republican<\/strong> perspective.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"instructions\"><strong>How to read this debate:<\/strong> Each argument will appear one at a time. Click <em>&quot;Show next argument&quot;<\/em> to reveal the next turn. You will be asked questions about this conversation afterward, so please read carefully.<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-row\">\n<div class=\"progress-track\">\n<div class=\"progress-fill\" id=\"progress-fill\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-label\" id=\"progress-label\">0 \/ 6 arguments<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"bubble-area\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"typing-row\">\n<div class=\"dot-row\"><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><\/div>\n<span id=\"typing-name\">Individual A<\/span><\/div>\n<button id=\"continue-btn\">Show next argument &rarr;<\/button>\n\n<div id=\"completion-banner\">\u2713 You&#39;ve read all 6 arguments. You may now proceed to the questions.<\/div>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"startDem","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Abortion Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Democratic per...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID83","QuestionJS":"Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnload(function()\n{\n    var bubbles = [\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I appreciate you raising this issue. I believe policies that curtail reproductive rights and access to reproductive healthcare are unjust and should not be implemented, or even be advertised as \\\"pro-life\\\". The decision to ban 'abortion' has been shown to have severe repercussions upon a woman's ability to receive critical or life-saving healthcare, which may necessarily involve an abortion.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I don't understand your perspective and concern about access to reproductive rights. In the context of abortion, the 14th Amendment to the constitution would classify fertilized eggs or \\\"unborn children\\\" as full-fledged citizens who deserve all of the rights and protections afforded by the U.S. constitution. This is not consistent with the act of abortion as the unborn child has a fundamental right to life which cannot be infringed.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"That point is redundant in this case. Restricting access to reproductive rights should make us first consider women's ability to receive healthcare if needed. If extreme and dangerous bans are put in place, potentially even those that include no exception for rape or incest, the health and lives of women are jeopardised, often forcing women to travel hundreds of miles for care. I've come across evidence that has found that since Roe vs. Wade was overturned, the majority of women were concerned about access to abortion if it was needed to preserve their life or health.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"The concern for women's health is not valid. I think that beyond the women's ability to make a decision, another human, in this case the unborn child, is affected by the women's choice to abort. Although prohibiting abortion might seem to put the rights of fetuses as more valuable than those of grown women, I don\u2019t see it that way as the right to not be murdered should be more fundamental than the right to not get pregnant.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I don't understand your point about the unborn child's right and why you bring that into the discussion. I think that sometimes in some cases women might not be ready or prepared to have a child and by allowing them to make a decision about what to do might prevent the child from future misery. In the end, the state should not act as a paternalistic figure and make the decision for the women in question. Rather, women should be able to make the decision on their own.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"Your point about pregnancies being unplanned and how that could affect women's and babies' physical and mental health should not matter. Abortions and the laws that govern them are programs and projects that do not respect human life and conscious rights and that undermine family formation.\"\n  }\n];\n    var currentIndex = 0, bubbleTimings = [], bubbleStart = null, tabSwitches = 0, pageStart = Date.now();\n    var ED_KEY = 'abo_UU_D';\n\n   document.addEventListener('visibilitychange', function() { if (document.hidden) tabSwitches++; });\n\n    function setEmbeddedData(key, value) {\n        if (typeof Qualtrics !== 'undefined' && Qualtrics.SurveyEngine)\n            Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(key, String(value));\n    }\n\n    function updateProgress(shown) {\n        document.getElementById('progress-fill').style.width = (shown \/ bubbles.length * 100) + '%';\n        document.getElementById('progress-label').textContent = shown + ' \/ ' + bubbles.length + ' arguments';\n    }\n\n    function renderBubble(index) {\n        var b = bubbles[index], area = document.getElementById('bubble-area');\n        if (index === 2 || index === 4) {\n            var hr = document.createElement('div'); hr.className = 'turn-divider'; area.appendChild(hr);\n        }\n        var div = document.createElement('div');\n        div.className = 'bubble ' + b.side;\n        div.innerHTML = '<span class=\"speaker-tag\">' + b.speaker + '<\/span><span class=\"bubble-text\">\\u201c' + b.text + '\\u201d<\/span>';\n        area.appendChild(div);\n        setTimeout(function() { div.scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'nearest'}); }, 100);\n    }\n\n    function showTypingThen(index, callback) {\n        var row = document.getElementById('typing-row'), name = document.getElementById('typing-name');\n        name.textContent = bubbles[index].speaker.split('\\u2014')[0].trim();\n        row.style.display = 'flex';\n        row.classList.add('visible');\n        setTimeout(function() { row.classList.remove('visible'); row.style.display = 'none'; setTimeout(callback, 80); }, 1600);\n    }\n\n    function showNextBubble() {\n        if (bubbleStart !== null) {\n            bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n            setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n        }\n        document.getElementById('continue-btn').style.display = 'none';\n        var idx = currentIndex++;\n        showTypingThen(idx, function() {\n            renderBubble(idx); updateProgress(currentIndex); bubbleStart = Date.now();\n            if (currentIndex < bubbles.length) {\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n                    btn.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                    btn.textContent = 'Show next argument \u2192';\n                }, 600);\n            } else {\n                bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_tab_switches', tabSwitches);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_total_ms', Date.now() - pageStart);\n                window._debateBubbles = bubbles;\n                setEmbeddedData('debateJSON', JSON.stringify(bubbles));\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    document.getElementById('completion-banner').style.display = 'block';\n                    var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                }, 500);\n            }\n        });\n    }\n\n   \/* expose to addOnReady *\/\n    window._qdb_init = function() {\n        var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'none';\n        updateProgress(0);\n        setTimeout(function() { document.getElementById('typing-row').style.display = 'flex'; showNextBubble(); }, 600);\n    };\n    window._qdb_next = showNextBubble;\n    window.showNextBubble = showNextBubble;  \/\/ \u2190 ADD THIS LINE\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function()\n{\n    if (window._qdb_init) window._qdb_init();\n    \n    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n    if (btn) btn.addEventListener('click', function() { window._qdb_next(); });\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnUnload(function()\n{\n    \/* cleanup *\/\n});"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID84","SecondaryAttribute":"Abortion Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Republican per..","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div class=\"debate-container\">\n<div class=\"page-header\">\n<div class=\"label\">Abortion Policy &middot; Turn-by-turn debate<\/div>\n\n<h1>Hypothetical Discussion<\/h1>\n\n<p>Individual A holds a <strong>Republican<\/strong> perspective; Individual B holds a <strong>Democratic<\/strong> perspective.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"instructions\"><strong>How to read this debate:<\/strong> Each argument will appear one at a time. Click <em>&quot;Show next argument&quot;<\/em> to reveal the next turn. You will be asked questions about this conversation afterward, so please read carefully.<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-row\">\n<div class=\"progress-track\">\n<div class=\"progress-fill\" id=\"progress-fill\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div class=\"progress-label\" id=\"progress-label\">0 \/ 6 arguments<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"bubble-area\">&nbsp;<\/div>\n\n<div id=\"typing-row\">\n<div class=\"dot-row\"><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><span>&nbsp;<\/span><\/div>\n<span id=\"typing-name\">Individual A<\/span><\/div>\n<button id=\"continue-btn\">Show next argument &rarr;<\/button>\n\n<div id=\"completion-banner\">\u2713 You&#39;ve read all 6 arguments. You may now proceed to the questions.<\/div>\n<\/div>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"startRep","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Abortion Policy \u00b7 Turn-by-turn debate Hypothetical Discussion Individual A holds a Republican per...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID84","QuestionJS":"Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnload(function()\n{\n    var bubbles = [\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I appreciate you raising this issue. I think policies that curtail reproductive rights and access to reproductive healthcare are just and should be implemented across the country. In the context of abortion, the 14th Amendment to the constitution would classify fertilized eggs or \\\"unborn children\\\" as full-fledged citizens who deserve all of the rights and protections afforded by the U.S. constitution. This is not consistent with the act of abortion as the unborn child has a fundamental right to life which cannot be infringed.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"I don't understand your perspective and concern about the rights of the unborn child. Still, the decision to ban 'abortion' has been shown to have severe repercussions upon a woman's ability to receive critical or life-saving healthcare, which may necessarily involve an abortion.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"That point should not matter in this context. The rights of the unborn child, who cannot speak up themselves, should not be diminished. I think that beyond the women's ability to make a decision, another human, in this case the unborn child, is affected by the women's choice to abort. Although prohibiting abortion might seem to put the rights of fetuses as more valuable than those of grown women, I don\u2019t see it that way as the right to not be murdered should be more fundamental than the right to not get pregnant.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"The concern for the child's health is irrelevant. Restricting access to reproductive rights should make us first consider women's ability to receive healthcare if needed. If extreme and dangerous bans are put in place, potentially even those that include no exception for rape or incest, the health and lives of women are jeopardised, often forcing women to travel hundreds of miles for care. I've come across evidence that has found that since Roe vs. Wade was overturned, the majority of women were concerned about access to abortion if it was needed to preserve their life or health.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual A \u2014 Republican perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"rep\",\n    \"text\": \"I don't understand your point about the mother's rights and why you bring that into the discussion. Still, I think that abortions and the laws that govern them are programs and projects that do not respect human life and conscious rights and that undermine family formation.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"speaker\": \"Individual B \u2014 Democratic perspective\",\n    \"side\": \"dem\",\n    \"text\": \"Your point about family formation is unfair. I think that sometimes in some cases women might not be ready or prepared to have a child and by allowing them to make a decision about what to do might prevent the child from future misery. In the end, the state should not act as a paternalistic figure and make the decision for the women in question. Rather, women should be able to make the decision on their own.\"\n  }\n];\n    var currentIndex = 0, bubbleTimings = [], bubbleStart = null, tabSwitches = 0, pageStart = Date.now();\n    var ED_KEY = 'abo_UU_R';\n\n    document.addEventListener('visibilitychange', function() { if (document.hidden) tabSwitches++; });\n\n    function setEmbeddedData(key, value) {\n        if (typeof Qualtrics !== 'undefined' && Qualtrics.SurveyEngine)\n            Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(key, String(value));\n    }\n\n    function updateProgress(shown) {\n        document.getElementById('progress-fill').style.width = (shown \/ bubbles.length * 100) + '%';\n        document.getElementById('progress-label').textContent = shown + ' \/ ' + bubbles.length + ' arguments';\n    }\n\n    function renderBubble(index) {\n        var b = bubbles[index], area = document.getElementById('bubble-area');\n        if (index === 2 || index === 4) {\n            var hr = document.createElement('div'); hr.className = 'turn-divider'; area.appendChild(hr);\n        }\n        var div = document.createElement('div');\n        div.className = 'bubble ' + b.side;\n        div.innerHTML = '<span class=\"speaker-tag\">' + b.speaker + '<\/span><span class=\"bubble-text\">\\u201c' + b.text + '\\u201d<\/span>';\n        area.appendChild(div);\n        setTimeout(function() { div.scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'nearest'}); }, 100);\n    }\n\n    function showTypingThen(index, callback) {\n        var row = document.getElementById('typing-row'), name = document.getElementById('typing-name');\n        name.textContent = bubbles[index].speaker.split('\\u2014')[0].trim();\n        row.style.display = 'flex';\n        row.classList.add('visible');\n        setTimeout(function() { row.classList.remove('visible'); row.style.display = 'none'; setTimeout(callback, 80); }, 1600);\n    }\n\n    function showNextBubble() {\n        if (bubbleStart !== null) {\n            bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n            setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n        }\n        document.getElementById('continue-btn').style.display = 'none';\n        var idx = currentIndex++;\n        showTypingThen(idx, function() {\n            renderBubble(idx); updateProgress(currentIndex); bubbleStart = Date.now();\n            if (currentIndex < bubbles.length) {\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n                    btn.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                    btn.textContent = 'Show next argument \u2192';\n                }, 600);\n            } else {\n                bubbleTimings.push(Date.now() - bubbleStart);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_timings', JSON.stringify(bubbleTimings));\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_tab_switches', tabSwitches);\n                setEmbeddedData(ED_KEY + '_total_ms', Date.now() - pageStart);\n                window._debateBubbles = bubbles;\n                setEmbeddedData('debateJSON', JSON.stringify(bubbles));\n                setTimeout(function() {\n                    document.getElementById('completion-banner').style.display = 'block';\n                    var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'inline-block';\n                }, 500);\n            }\n        });\n    }\n\n   \/* expose to addOnReady *\/\n    window._qdb_init = function() {\n        var nb = document.getElementById('NextButton'); if (nb) nb.style.display = 'none';\n        updateProgress(0);\n        setTimeout(function() { document.getElementById('typing-row').style.display = 'flex'; showNextBubble(); }, 600);\n    };\n    window._qdb_next = showNextBubble;\n    window.showNextBubble = showNextBubble;  \/\/ \u2190 ADD THIS LINE\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function()\n{\n    if (window._qdb_init) window._qdb_init();\n    \n    var btn = document.getElementById('continue-btn');\n    if (btn) btn.addEventListener('click', function() { window._qdb_next(); });\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnUnload(function()\n{\n    \/* cleanup *\/\n});"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID85","SecondaryAttribute":"\u25b6 Review the debate conversation Loading debate... We would like to get your feelings toward both.","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<div id=\"debate-accordion\" style=\"margin-bottom:24px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;\n            border-radius:8px;overflow:hidden;\n            font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,\n            'Segoe UI',sans-serif;\"><button id=\"toggle-debate-btn\" style=\"width:100%;padding:14px 20px;text-align:left;\n                 background:#f9fafb;border:none;cursor:pointer;\n                 font-size:14px;font-weight:600;color:#374151;\n                 display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;\n                 transition:background 0.15s;\"><span id=\"accordion-arrow\" style=\"display:inline-block;transition:transform 0.2s;\n                 font-size:12px;\">\u25b6<\/span> Review the debate conversation<\/button>\n<div id=\"debate-content\" style=\"display:none;padding:20px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;\n              background:#ffffff;max-height:400px;overflow-y:auto;\">\n<p style=\"color:#6b7280;font-size:13px;font-style:italic;\n              margin-top:0;\">Loading debate...<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\nWe would like to get your feelings toward both Individual A and Individual B. We would like you to rate them using something we call the feeling thermometer.<br \/>\n<br \/>\nRatings between 50 degrees and 100 degrees mean that you feel favorable and warm toward them. Ratings between 0 degrees and 50 degrees mean that you don&#39;t feel favorable toward them and that you don&#39;t care too much for them. You would rate them at the 50-degree mark if you don&#39;t feel particularly warm or cold toward them.","QuestionJS":"Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnload(function() {\n    var qid = this.questionId;\n    var debateOpened = 0;\n    var toggleCount = 0;\n    var firstOpenTime = null;\n    var pageStart = Date.now();\n\n    \/\/ Share these on window so addOnUnload can access them\n    window._accordion_totalViewTime = 0;\n    window._accordion_viewStart = null;\n    window._accordion_qid = qid;\n\n    function setED(key, value) {\n        Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(key, String(value));\n    }\n\n    \/\/ --- Load debate content from Embedded Data ---\n    var debateHTML = \"${e:\/\/Field\/debateHTML}\";\n    var contentDiv = document.getElementById('debate-content');\n    if (contentDiv && debateHTML && debateHTML !== '') {\n        contentDiv.innerHTML = debateHTML;\n    } else if (contentDiv) {\n        contentDiv.innerHTML =\n            '<p style=\"color:#999;font-style:italic;\">'\n            + 'Debate transcript not available.<\/p>';\n    }\n\n    \/\/ --- Toggle function ---\n    window.toggleDebate = function() {\n        var content = document.getElementById('debate-content');\n        var arrow = document.getElementById('accordion-arrow');\n        if (!content) return;\n\n        if (content.style.display === 'none') {\n            content.style.display = 'block';\n            if (arrow) arrow.style.transform = 'rotate(90deg)';\n            debateOpened = 1;\n            toggleCount++;\n            window._accordion_viewStart = Date.now();\n            if (firstOpenTime === null) {\n                firstOpenTime = Date.now() - pageStart;\n                setED(qid + '_accordion_firstOpen_ms', firstOpenTime);\n            }\n        } else {\n            content.style.display = 'none';\n            if (arrow) arrow.style.transform = 'rotate(0deg)';\n            if (window._accordion_viewStart) {\n                window._accordion_totalViewTime += Date.now() - window._accordion_viewStart;\n                window._accordion_viewStart = null;\n            }\n        }\n        setED(qid + '_accordion_opened', debateOpened);\n        setED(qid + '_accordion_toggles', toggleCount);\n    };\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnReady(function() {\n    \/\/ Set default slider values to 50 (only relevant for thermometer)\n    var qid = this.questionId;\n    var sliders = document.querySelectorAll('#' + qid + ' .slider-container input[type=\"range\"]');\n    sliders.forEach(function(slider) {\n        slider.value = 50;\n        slider.dispatchEvent(new Event('input'));\n        slider.dispatchEvent(new Event('change'));\n    });\n});\n\nQualtrics.SurveyEngine.addOnUnload(function() {\n    \/\/ If accordion was still open when leaving, count that time\n    if (window._accordion_viewStart) {\n        window._accordion_totalViewTime += Date.now() - window._accordion_viewStart;\n        window._accordion_viewStart = null;\n    }\n    Qualtrics.SurveyEngine.setEmbeddedData(\n        window._accordion_qid + '_accordion_viewTime_ms',\n        String(window._accordion_totalViewTime || 0)\n    );\n});","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"Q85","QuestionType":"Slider","Selector":"HSLIDER","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","CSSliderMin":0,"CSSliderMax":100,"GridLines":10,"SnapToGrid":false,"NumDecimals":"0","ShowValue":true,"CustomStart":false,"SliderStartPositions":{"1":0,"2":0},"NotApplicable":false,"MobileFirst":true},"QuestionDescription":"\u25b6 Review the debate conversation Loading debate... We would like to get your feelings toward both...","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"How would you rate Individual A?"},"2":{"Display":"How would you rate Individual B?"}},"ChoiceOrder":[1,2],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":3,"NextAnswerId":1,"Labels":[],"QuestionID":"QID85"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID9","SecondaryAttribute":"Please indicate your annual household income.","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Please indicate your annual household income.","DataExportTag":"IncomeQuestion","QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"SAVR","SubSelector":"TX","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Please indicate your annual household income.","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"Less than $50K"},"2":{"Display":"$50K - $99K"},"3":{"Display":"$100K - $149K"},"4":{"Display":"$150K - $199K"},"5":{"Display":"$200K or above"},"6":{"Display":"Prefer not to answer"}},"ChoiceOrder":[1,2,3,4,5,6],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":7,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID9"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_9odEiuuhBFfakNE","Element":"STAT","PrimaryAttribute":"Survey Statistics","SecondaryAttribute":null,"TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"MobileCompatible":true,"ID":"Survey Statistics"}}]}